\h Yohan
\toc1 Yohan (John)
\toc2 Yohan
\toc3 Jhn
\mt2 The account of Yeshua's ministry by
\mt1 Yohan (John)
\is1 Introduction
\is2 Author
\ip This account about the works and teachings of Yeshua (Jesus) was written by Yohan (John), brother of Yacob (mistakenly known in older English Bibles as James). Both of them were in the small group of twelve close followers of Yeshua that he selected as his apprentices and who accompanied him around as he taught. Out of the twelve, Yohan was the one that greatly loved Yeshua, and his closeness gave him much of the insight that he includes with his description of Yeshua's actions and teaching. The two brothers were the sons of Zebedee, and all three of them worked as fishermen on Lake Galilee.
\is2 This account
\ip The \em Open English Translation\em* places Yohan's account before the others because it begins with the eternal existence of Yeshua the messiah. Not only is Yeshua the godly messenger, he was also the creator who has now descended from heaven as a man. Omitting any mention of the baby Yeshua, Yohan does however tell us about Yohan-the-immerser who came before Yeshua to prepare the people for the arrival of the promised messiah.
\ip In chapters two to twelve it's written how the various miracles that Yeshua did showed that he was the promised messiah who would offer life without ending to anyone who would accept that he had been sent by God and trust in his teaching. Although there were indeed many who did believe in him, many others were unable to come to that point and ended up opposing Yeshua at every turn.
\ip In chapters thirteen to seventeen, the compassion of Yeshua towards his followers is described. He also told them in advance of his impending brutal death.
\ip In the final few chapters, we read about the arrest and judging of Yeshua, his being fastened to a pole and giving up his spirit, his coming back to life, and how his followers saw him and spoke with him again during that period.
\ip Yohan is careful to explain how to receive life without ending by means of believing that Yeshua came down from heaven and obeying his teaching. Yeshua himself is the path and the truth and the life (14:6).
\iot Main components of Yohan's account
\io1 Introduction \ior 1:1-18\ior*
\io1 Yohan-the-immerser and the first followers of Yeshua \ior 1:19-51\ior*
\io1 The people monitor Yeshua's teaching and miracles \ior 2:1вҖ“12:50\ior*
\io1 Yeshua's final week in and around Yerushalem \ior 13:1вҖ“19:42\ior*
\io1 Yeshua comes back to life and meets people again \ior 20:1-31\ior*
\io1 Yeshua reveals himself to his followers in Galilee \ior 21:1-25\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 The arrival of the true light
\rem /s1 The Word Became Flesh; The Word of Life; The coming of Christ; Christ, the Eternal Word
\p
\v 1 In the beginningВҰ62339 was the message,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft TD: This passage is complex to translate because the message was also the messengerвҖ”that is, Yeshua came not only to teach about getting saved, but also to become the actual way to be saved!\f* and the message was with God, and the message was \add and is\add* God.
\v 2 He, \add the message\add*, was with \nd GodВҰ62362\nd* \add even\add* at the creationВҰ62359 \add of the universe\add*.
\v 3 Everything came into existence throughВҰ62364 the messenger\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Lit. him.\f*вҖ”\add вүҲthere's not even one thing that came into existence that wasn't made by\add* him.
\v 4 He holds life, and that life is the lightВҰ62387 of humankind.
\v 5 And that lightВҰ62392 is shiningВҰ62396 in the darkness, andВҰ62390 darkness cannot overcome him.
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6: \xt Mat 3:1; Mrk 1:4; Luk 3:1-2.\x*A manВҰ62404 arrived who had been sentВҰ62405 by \nd GodВҰ62409\nd*. His nameВҰ62412 was Yohan.
\v 7 He came as a testimonyВҰ62420 to tell about the light so that everyone would believeВҰ62428 the light.
\v 8 Yohan himself wasn't the lightвҖ”he was merely the announcer of the light.
\v 9 The true lightВҰ62445 whichВҰ62448 enlightensВҰ62449 everyВҰ62450 personВҰ62451 was comingВҰ62452 into the worldВҰ62455.
\p
\v 10 He was in the world and he's the creator of the world, and yet the world didn'tВҰ62472 even know him.
\v 11 He cameВҰ62477 to his own chosen people, butВҰ62478 they wouldn't accept himВҰ62481,
\v 12 however anyone who would accept him and trusted in hisВҰ62501 authority, he gaveВҰ62488 them the rightВҰ62492 to becomeВҰ62495 childrenВҰ62493 of \nd GodВҰ62494\nd*вҖ”
\v 13 not physical children and not coming from human actions, butВҰ62514 children of \nd GodВҰ62516\nd*.
\p
\v 14 And the messageВҰ62521 becameВҰ62523 a human and lived here amongВҰ62526 us and weВҰ62529 sawВҰ62529 hisВҰ62532 greatnessвҖ”the greatness of an only child of the fatherВҰ62537вҖ”full of graceВҰ62540 and truthВҰ62542.
\p
\v 15 Yohan explained about him and loudly told everyone, вҖң\add вүҲHe's\add* the one I meant when I saidВҰ62554, вҖҳThere's someone comingВҰ62560 afterВҰ62558 me, yet who came before me, becauseВҰ62565 he existed before I did!вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 16 BecauseВҰ62569 he has so much, we all receivedВҰ62578 grace and then even more grace.
\v 17 The commands came to us through Mosheh, butВҰ62593 graceВҰ62592 and truthВҰ62595 came to us through \nd Yeshua\nd* the \nd messiahВҰ62598\nd*.
\v 18 No one has ever actually seenВҰ62602 God, but the human son born from God the fatherВҰ62617 and in close touch with him, he was the one to explainВҰ62619 God to us.
\s1 The interrogation of Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 John the Baptist's Message; The Testimony of John the Baptist; John the Baptist Denies Being the Christ; Testimony of the Baptist and the first disciples
\r (Mat. 3:1-12; Mark 1:1-8; Luke 3:1-18)
\p
\v 19 Yohan explained some of this when the Jewish leaders sentВҰ62629 out priestsВҰ62637 andВҰ62638 temple workers from Yerushalem to askВҰ62643 himВҰ62646, вҖңWho are youВҰ62648?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 He didn'tВҰ62654 flinch from the truth andВҰ62651 so he told them, вҖңI am not the \nd chosenВҰ62664 messiahВҰ62664\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 1:21: a \xt Mal 4:5; \xo b \xt Deu 18:15,18.\x*SoВҰ62665 they asked him again, вҖңAre you Eliyah come back to life?вҖқ
\p And he answered, вҖңNo, I'm not.вҖқ
\p They asked, вҖңAre you the prophetВҰ62687?вҖқ
\p Again he answered, вҖңNo, I'm not.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 SoВҰ62694 they asked himВҰ62695, вҖңWho are you then? We need to giveВҰ62701 an answerВҰ62700 to the ones who sentВҰ62703 us. How do you describe yourselfВҰ62709?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 1:23: \xt Isa 40:3 (LXX).\x*So he said, вҖңI am a voiceВҰ62712 shoutingВҰ62713\f + \fr 1:23 \ft We've deliberately omitted putting a comma here, because it's also possible that the comma should go after вҖҳwildernessвҖҷ.\f* in the wilderness smooth the pathВҰ62719 of \nd YahwehВҰ62720\nd*, as the prophetВҰ62730 Yeshayah said.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 Some of the ones sentВҰ62733 out were members of the Pharisee partyВҰ62737.
\v 25 These ones askedВҰ62739 Yohan, вҖңSoВҰ62738 why are you immersingВҰ62746 people thenВҰ62738 if you aren'tВҰ62749 the \nd messiahВҰ62752\nd* or Eliyah or the prophetВҰ62759?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 He answeredВҰ62760, вҖңI'm immersingВҰ62766 people in waterВҰ62770, but somewhere here among us all there's someone you don'tВҰ62779 knowвҖ”
\v 27 the one comingВҰ62786 afterВҰ62784 me, and I'm not even good enough to untieВҰ62799 hisВҰ62800 sandalВҰ62805 strapsВҰ62803!вҖқ
\p
\v 28 All this happened in BethanyВҰ62810 on the east side of the YordanВҰ62815 River whereВҰ62817 Yohan was immersingВҰ62821 people.
\s1 Yeshua gets publicly revealed
\rem /s1 Jesus, the Lamb of God
\p
\v 29 The next dayВҰ62824 Yohan saw \nd Yeshua\nd* comingВҰ62831 towards himВҰ62833, andВҰ62834 said, вҖңHey! Here's the sacrificial lambВҰ62838 of \nd GodВҰ62840\nd* who's come to take away the sinВҰ62845 of the worldВҰ62848.
\v 30 This is the manВҰ62861 I was talking about when I saidВҰ62855, вҖҳThere's someone comingВҰ62860 after me, yet who came before me, becauseВҰ62866 heВҰ62869 existed before I did.вҖҷ
\v 31 I didn'tВҰ62871 know who he was butВҰ62874 nevertheless I cameВҰ62882 andВҰ62870 immersedВҰ62887 people in waterВҰ62886 so that this man could be revealedВҰ62876 to \add all\add* Yisrael.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 And Yohan further explained, вҖңI saw God's \nd spiritВҰ62896\nd* come down andВҰ62905 settle on himВҰ62909.
\v 33 I didn'tВҰ62913 know which one was him, butВҰ62910 the one who sent me to immerse people in waterВҰ62923 said, вҖҳWhenВҰ62910 you see the spirit comingВҰ62935 down andВҰ62910 settling on someone, he is the one who will immerse people with God's holy spirit.вҖҷ
\v 34 And I have seenВҰ62952 that, andВҰ62951 so I can assure you that he is God's son.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua gets a few followers
\rem /s1 The First Disciples of Jesus; Jesus' First Disciples
\p
\v 35 The next dayВҰ62964, Yohan was back there with twoВҰ62975 of hisВҰ62974 apprenticesВҰ62973
\v 36 andВҰ62976 noticing \nd Yeshua\nd* walkingВҰ62980 nearby he said, вҖңLookВҰ62982! There's the \add sacrificial\add* lambВҰ62984 of \nd GodВҰ62986\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 37 WhenВҰ62995 hisВҰ63001 twoВҰ63000 apprenticesВҰ63002 heardВҰ62996 him say that, they left him andВҰ62995 followedВҰ63007 \nd YeshuaВҰ63009\nd*.
\v 38 ButВҰ63024 \nd Yeshua\nd* turnedВҰ63010 and saw them followingВҰ63017 him, and asked them, вҖң\wj What do you two want?\wj*вҖқ
\p And they saidВҰ63025 to him, вҖңTeacherВҰ63032, where do you live?вҖқ
\p
\v 39 вҖң\wj Come and see,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua replied. SoВҰ63042 they wentВҰ63041 with him and sawВҰ63044 whereВҰ63045 he lived, and then they stayed there that night, because it was already late afternoon.
\p
\v 40 AndrewВҰ63062, the brotherВҰ63064 of SimonВҰ63065 PeterВҰ63066 was one of those twoВҰ63071 who heardВҰ63073 Yohan andВҰ63076 then followedВҰ63077 Yeshua.
\v 41 As soon as he found his brotherВҰ63085, he said to SimonВҰ63088, вҖңWe have found the messiahвҖ”God's chosen one,вҖқ
\v 42 and led him to Yeshua. When Yeshua saw him, he saidВҰ63113, вҖң\wj Ah, you are SimonВҰ63117, Yohan's son, but from now on you'll be calledВҰ63123 Peter whichВҰ63125 means \+it stone\+it*.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Philip and Nathanael join the group
\rem /s1 Jesus Calls Philip and Nathanael
\p
\v 43 The followingВҰ63146 dayВҰ63129, \nd Yeshua\nd* wantedВҰ63131 to go to GalileeВҰ63137. He found PhilipВҰ63140 andВҰ63141 told himВҰ63143, вҖң\wj Follow me!\wj*вҖқ
\v 44 PhilipВҰ63151 was from the townВҰ63156 of BethsaidaВҰ63153 where AndrewВҰ63158 andВҰ63159 PeterВҰ63160 lived.
\v 45 Philip then found \nd NathanaelВҰ63164\nd* and told himВҰ63167, вҖңWe'veВҰ63177 found the one that Mosheh and the prophetsВҰ63176 wroteВҰ63169 about in the Scriptures. He's \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ63187\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 46 And \nd NathanaelВҰ63191\nd* saidВҰ63189, вҖңDoes anything goodВҰ63196 come from \nd NazarethВҰ63193\nd*?вҖқ
\p SoВҰ63188 PhilipВҰ63202 answered, вҖңWell, come andВҰ63204 seeВҰ63205 \add for yourself\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 47 \nd Yeshua\nd* sawВҰ63206 \nd NathanaelВҰ63212\nd* approaching andВҰ63216 said, вҖң\wj Ah, this is an honest IsraeliВҰ63224.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 48 ButВҰ63239 \nd NathanaelВҰ63232\nd* queried him, вҖңWhere do you know \em me\em* from?вҖқ
\p And \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj Actually I sawВҰ63251 you underВҰ63248 that figВҰ63250 treeВҰ63250 before PhilipВҰ63245 had even called you.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 49 \nd NathanaelВҰ63255\nd* exclaimed, вҖңGreat teacher! You \em are\em* God's son! You're the kingВҰ63271 of Yisrael!вҖқ
\p
\v 50 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ63279, вҖң\wj So you believeВҰ63293 this because I said that I had seen you under the figВҰ63291 treeВҰ63291. You'll get to see much greaterВҰ63294 things than that!\wj*вҖқ
\v 51 \x + \xo 1:51: \xt Gen 28:12.\x*And he continued, вҖң\wj Honestly, I'm telling all of you: you'll be seeingВҰ63309 the sky openedВҰ63312 up and God's messengersВҰ63315 goingВҰ63318 up and comingВҰ63320 down on meвҖ”humanity's child.\wj*вҖқ
\c 2
\s1 The wine miracle
\rem /s1 The Wedding in Cana; The Wedding at Cana; Jesus Changes Water to Wine; Signs and discourses
\p
\v 1 On the Tuesday\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Or possibly, вҖҳThree days laterвҖҷ.\f*, there was a weddingВҰ63332 in CanaВҰ63337 in GalileeВҰ63339, andВҰ63340 \nd Yeshua's\nd* motherВҰ63343 was there
\v 2 and \nd YeshuaВҰ63351\nd* and hisВҰ63356 apprenticesВҰ63355 were also invitedВҰ63347.
\v 3 WhenВҰ63360 the wine ran out at the wedding, his motherВҰ63376 said to himВҰ63381, вҖңThey haven't got any more wine.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj What does that have to do with us, mother? It's not the time for myВҰ63402 ministry yet.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 5 But hisВҰ63406 motherВҰ63405 told the servantsВҰ63408, вҖңJust do whateverВҰ63409 he tells you.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 Now there were sixВҰ63423 empty stoneВҰ63421 waterВҰ63422 jars there that are used for Jewish purificationВҰ63427 ceremonies. (Each one could hold over 70 litres.)
\v 7 SoВҰ63448 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them to fill the jars with waterВҰ63447, andВҰ63448 theyВҰ63449 filledВҰ63449 them up.
\v 8 ThenВҰ63453 he said, вҖң\wj Okay, now take a sample out andВҰ63453 give it to the MC.\wj*вҖқ SoВҰ63453 they took some
\v 9 andВҰ63467 when the MC tastedВҰ63468 the water that had now turned to wine, not knowingВҰ63477 whereВҰ63478 it had come from he called the groom
\v 10 and exclaimed, вҖңMost people supply the best wine at the beginning \add of the reception\add*, and the cheaper stuff when people are a bit tipsy. ButВҰ63494 you'veВҰ63511 keptВҰ63513 the best wine untilВҰ63517 last!вҖқ
\p
\v 11 This event in CanaВҰ63530, GalileeВҰ63533, was the first of the miracles that \nd Yeshua\nd* did, and it revealedВҰ63536 his greatness and his followers believedВҰ63541 that he was from God.
\rem /s1 Jesus Clears the Temple
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 2:12: \xt Mat 4:13.\x*AfterВҰ63550 that, Yeshua and his motherВҰ63563 and brothersВҰ63567 and his followers travelled east to CapernaumВҰ63555, butВҰ63561 theyВҰ63575 only stayed thereВҰ63574 a few daysВҰ63579.
\s1 Yeshua disturbs the temple traders
\rem /s1 Jesus Goes to the Temple; Jesus Cleanses the Temple; Jesus Clears the Temple
\r (Mat. 21:12-13; Mark 11:15-17; Luke 19:45-46)
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 2:13: \xt Exo 12:1-27.\x*By thenВҰ63580 it was getting close to the time of the Jewish Festival of the Passover, andВҰ63588 \nd Yeshua\nd* wentВҰ63589 down to Yerushalem.
\v 14 There in the templeВҰ63601, he discovered merchants sellingВҰ63603 cowsВҰ63605 and sheepВҰ63608 and dovesВҰ63612, and moneychangersВҰ63616 sittingВҰ63617 at their tables.
\v 15 Yeshua formed some cordsВҰ63624 into a whip and drove the sheepВҰ63635 and cowsВҰ63638 out of the templeВҰ63630 grounds, and he overturnedВҰ63651 the tablesВҰ63649вҖ”spilling the coinsВҰ63646 of the moneychangersВҰ63641 onto the ground.
\v 16 He scolded the ones sellingВҰ63658 dovesВҰ63657, saying, вҖң\wj Get them out of here! Don't be makingВҰ63665 myВҰ63670 father'sВҰ63669 house into a market.\wj*вҖқ
\v 17 \x + \xo 2:17: \xt Psa 69:9.\x*That remindedВҰ63675 hisВҰ63679 followers of the scripture: вҖңI'll be filled with zeal for yourВҰ63690 temple.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 Then the Jewish leaders respondedВҰ63699, вҖңDo a miracle to show that you have the authority to do theseВҰ63706 things.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \x + \xo 2:19: \xt Mat 26:61; 27:40; Mrk 14:58; 15:29.\x*ButВҰ63711 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ63708, вҖң\wj Well, destroy this templeВҰ63716 and I'llВҰ63722 raise\wj*\f + \fr 2:19 \ft We couldn't easily use \+em rebuild\+em* here because there's a play on wordsвҖ”see verse 21.\f* \wj itВҰ63723 again in threeВҰ63720 daysВҰ63721.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 The leaders smirked, вҖңThis templeВҰ63734 took forty-six yearsВҰ63731 to build, and you reckon that you can raise itВҰ63744 again in threeВҰ63741 daysВҰ63742?вҖқ
\p
\v 21 But Yeshua had been meaning hisВҰ63754 own bodyВҰ63753 when he was talkingВҰ63748 about the templeВҰ63751.
\v 22 In the future when he was actually raisedВҰ63758 from the deadВҰ63760, hisВҰ63764 followers remembered this statement, and they believedВҰ63771 both the \add Hebrew\add* scripturesВҰ63773 and \nd Yeshua's\nd* messageВҰ63776.
\s1 Yeshua does miracles and knows thoughts
\rem /s1 Jesus' Knowledge of Human Nature
\p
\v 23 WhenВҰ63783 Yeshua was at the Passover Feast in Yerushalem, many believedВҰ63795 in hisВҰ63799 authority because they saw the miracles thatВҰ63804 he was able to do.
\v 24 But \nd Yeshua\nd* never fully entrustedВҰ63811 himself to them, becauseВҰ63817 he knew what people are like.
\v 25 (He didn't need anyoneВҰ63829 to tell him what people are like becauseВҰ63835 he could see what any personВҰ63844 was like on the inside.)
\c 3
\s1 Yeshua tells Nicodemus about the need to be reborn
\rem /s1 Nicodemus Visits Jesus; Jesus Teaches Nicodemus; Jesus and Nicodemus
\p
\v 1 After dark one evening, a Jewish leader named NicodemusВҰ63851 who was a member of the Pharisee partyВҰ63850
\v 2 wentВҰ63860 to Yeshua and saidВҰ63868, вҖңTeacher, we know that God has sent you as a teacherВҰ63876, becauseВҰ63879 no one could do those kinds of miracles if God wasn't with him.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ63902, вҖң\wj I'll tell youВҰ63908 frankly that no one can \+add get to\+add* seeВҰ63916 God's kingdomВҰ63918 unless he's reborn.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Nicodemus questioned, вҖңHow can an adult be reborn? A personВҰ63928 can'tВҰ63935 just return into their mother'sВҰ63941 womb andВҰ63945 then get born a secondВҰ63943 time!вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ButВҰ63962 \nd Yeshua\nd* continued, вҖң\wj Honestly, I'm tellingВҰ63953 youВҰ63954: unless a person is born from both waterВҰ63961 \+em andВҰ63962\+em* the \+nd spiritВҰ63963\+nd*, they can'tВҰ63956 enter God's kingdomВҰ63971.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Someone that's born from a bodyВҰ63982 is flesh \+add and bone\+add*, butВҰ63985 someone that's born from God's spirit is spiritual.\wj*
\v 7 \wj So you shouldn'tВҰ63993 be surprised that I told you that everyone needs to be reborn.\wj*
\v 8 \wj The wind blows wherever it wants, and you can hearВҰ64013 itsВҰ64012 soundВҰ64011 butВҰ64009 you can'tВҰ64015 actually see where it's comingВҰ64018 from or where it's goingВҰ64022 to. So too with everyoneВҰ64025 who's born from God's spirit.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Nicodemus replied, вҖңHow can all that even happen?вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖң\wj You're a Jewish teacherВҰ64052,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ64043, вҖң\wj and yet youВҰ64058 don'tВҰ64057 know all that?\wj*
\v 11 \wj It's true that we just teach what we know, and explain what we've seenВҰ64069 ourselves, butВҰ64067 you people aren'tВҰ64076 accepting ourВҰ64074 testimonyВҰ64073.\wj*
\v 12 \wj If I tell all of you earthlyВҰ64080 things and you don'tВҰ64085 believe them, how will you ever believe if I explain \+em heavenlyВҰ64093\+em* things \+add to you\+add*?\wj*
\v 13 \wj None of you have \+add ever\+add* gone up into heaven, butВҰ64096 I, humanity's child, have come down from heaven.\wj*
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 3:14: \xt Num 21:9.\x*вҖң\wj Just like Mosheh lifted up that \+add bronze\+add* snake \+add on a pole\+add* in the wildernessВҰ64129, it's \+add also\+add* necessaryВҰ64134 for humanity's child to be lifted up,\wj*\f + \fr 3:14 \ft lifted up / exalted: See https://bibleDifferences.net/2019/04/25/156-exulted\f*
\v 15 \wj so thatВҰ64142 everyoneВҰ64141 who believesВҰ64143 in himВҰ64147 won't die, but will live forever.\wj*\f + \fr 3:15 \ft See http://bibleandtech.blogspot.com/2021/03/john-314-21-translation-and-commentary.html\f*
\v 16 \wj Because\wj*\f + \fr 3:16 \ft Sadly when older English translations use вҖҳForвҖҷ (following John Wycliffe's middle-English translation from Latin from the 1300's), it's quite easy to ignore what it's there for. The \+em OET\+em* uses the modern-English translation вҖҳBecauseвҖҷ which makes the connection to the previous verses (especially v14-15) clearer.\f* \wj in that same way, \+nd GodВҰ64160\+nd* loves \+add the people of\+add* the world enough to cause \+add &his\+add* only son to be born, and to give himВҰ64177 to the world, so that everyoneВҰ64172 who believesВҰ64174 that won'tВҰ64178 die, butВҰ64181 will \+add go on to\+add* live forever.\wj*
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj \+nd GodВҰ64189\+nd* didn'tВҰ64185 send his son here to condemn people, butВҰ64201 rather to save them.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Anyone who trusts in me won'tВҰ64212 be condemned. However, anyone who doesn't believeВҰ64222 this has alreadyВҰ64218 been condemned becauseВҰ64220 he rejected the authority of the only son that \+nd GodВҰ64230\+nd* fathered.\wj*
\v 19 \wj And this is the verdict: that light has come into the worldВҰ64242, butВҰ64232 some peopleВҰ64247 love the darknessВҰ64251 more than the light becauseВҰ64257 they do evil things,\wj*
\v 20 \wj becauseВҰ64264 everyoneВҰ64263 who does evil things hates the light and doesn't come to the light so thatВҰ64265 their actions won'tВҰ64272 be exposed.\wj*
\v 21 \wj But anyone who does what is right, comes toward the lightВҰ64295 so that their actions can be revealedВҰ64297 as being done with God's help.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yohan approves of Yeshua's popularity
\rem /s1 Jesus and John the Baptist; John the Baptist Exalts Jesus; John the Baptist's Testimony About Jesus
\p
\v 22 AfterВҰ64308 this, \nd Yeshua\nd* and hisВҰ64320 followers wentВҰ64310 down to Yudea, and stayed thereВҰ64327 and immersedВҰ64332 some believers.
\v 23 YohanВҰ64337 was also immersingВҰ64338 people at AenonВҰ64340 near SalimВҰ64344 becauseВҰ64345 there was plenty of waterВҰ64346 there andВҰ64334 people would come \add to him\add* to get immersedВҰ64353.
\v 24 \x + \xo 3:24: \xt Mat 14:3; Mrk 6:17; Luk 3:19-20.\x*(At this point in time, Yohan had not yet been put in prisonВҰ64360.)
\v 25 Then a debateВҰ64366 aboutВҰ64376 purificationВҰ64377 started between Yohan's followers and a religious leader.\f + \fr 3:25 \ft https://www.billmounce.com/monday-with-mounce/what-does-the-word-%E2%80%9Cjew%E2%80%9D-mean-you-john-3-25\f*
\v 26 SoВҰ64378 some people wentВҰ64380 to Yohan and saidВҰ64385, вҖңTeacher, that man that cameВҰ64380 to you across the river and that you testifiedВҰ64398 about, now \em he's\em* immersingВҰ64402 people and so they're all going to him.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖңNone of us get anything if it's not being givenВҰ64426 from heavenВҰ64430,вҖқ Yohan answeredВҰ64408.
\v 28 \x + \xo 3:28: \xt Yhn 1:20.\x*вҖңYou yourselves know that I saidВҰ64436 that I'm not the \nd messiahВҰ64443\nd*, butВҰ64444 rather the one coming beforeВҰ64448 him.
\v 29 It's the groom that has the brideВҰ64454вҖ”the best man is happy becauseВҰ64470 he sees that the groom is happy. SoВҰ64476 I'm actually completely happy with all this.
\v 30 It's right and proper that he should increaseВҰ64485 and I should fade out.вҖқ
\rem /s1 He Who Comes from Heaven; The One Who Comes from Heaven
\p
\v 31 вҖңThe one who came down from heaven is greater than any of us. We came from this world and speakВҰ64511 in our earthly ways. The one who came down from heaven is greater than any of us.
\v 32 He explains about what he's seenВҰ64524 andВҰ64525 heardВҰ64526, butВҰ64529 people don't believe himВҰ64532.
\v 33 Anyone who does believe himВҰ64537, confirms that \nd GodВҰ64545\nd* is true.
\v 34 The one that God sentВҰ64550 tells us God's words, becauseВҰ64559 God doesn't ration his \nd spiritВҰ64567\nd*.
\v 35 \x + \xo 3:35: \xt Mat 11:27; Luk 10:22.\x*The fatherВҰ64569 loves the son and has put himВҰ64580 in charge of everything.
\v 36 Anyone who believesВҰ64583 \add God's\add* son will live forever, but anyone who disobeys the son won'tВҰ64596 be seeingВҰ64598 life, but will feel God's severeВҰ64602 angerВҰ64602 \add instead\add*.вҖқ
\c 4
\s1 Yeshua chats with a woman at the well
\rem /s1 Jesus Talks With a Samaritan Woman; Jesus and the Samaritan Woman; Jesus and the Woman of Samaria
\p
\v 1 When \nd Yeshua\nd* found out that the Pharisee partyВҰ64618 knewВҰ64611 that he was gaining and immersingВҰ64625 more followers than Yohan had,
\v 2 (although actually it wasn't \nd YeshuaВҰ64630\nd* himselfВҰ64631 that was immersingВҰ64634 them, butВҰ64635 hisВҰ64638 apprenticesВҰ64637 that were doing it),
\v 3 he left YudeaВҰ64641 and wentВҰ64644 back up to GalileeВҰ64648.
\v 4 On the way up, he decided to go through ShomronВҰ64655 \add (SamariaВҰ64655)\add*.
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 4:5: \xt Gen 33:19; Josh 24:32.\x*By choosing that route, they came to a townВҰ64659 in ShomronВҰ64661 calledВҰ64662 Sukar, whichВҰ64667 was near the place that the \add patriarch\add* Yosef had inherited from hisВҰ64675 father YacobВҰ64670,
\v 6 and вҖҳYacob's wellвҖҷ was thereВҰ64678. \nd Yeshua\nd* was tired from all the walking and was sittingВҰ64689 by the well around midday.
\p
\v 7 A womanВҰ64705 came from the town to get waterВҰ64710 from the well, and \nd Yeshua\nd* asked herВҰ64712 for a drinkВҰ64717
\v 8 since hisВҰ64721 followers had gone into the townВҰ64725 to buy some lunch.
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 4:9: \xt Est 4:1-5; Neh 4:1-2.\x*The woman said to him, вҖңYou're a Jew. How come you're asking me for a drinkВҰ64743 when I'm from Shomron?вҖқ (Jews don'tВҰ64751 normally associateВҰ64753 with anyone from Shomron.)
\p
\v 10 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ64757, вҖң\wj If you'd recognised God's giftВҰ64766 and who it is who's asking you for a drink, you would have asked me and I would have given you \+em livingВҰ64787\+em* waterВҰ64786 \+add to drink\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 11 ButВҰ64799 the womanВҰ64793 \add вүҲcountered\add*, вҖңMisterВҰ64794, you don't even have \add rope and\add* a bucketВҰ64797 to reach the water in the deep well. How then could you get вҖҳlivingВҰ64817 waterвҖҷ?
\v 12 I doubt that you're greaterВҰ64820 than ourВҰ64825 ancestor YacobВҰ64826 who made this well for us and drankВҰ64841 this water along with his children and his animals.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \nd Yeshua\nd* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ64854\add*, вҖң\wj EveryoneВҰ64857 who drinksВҰ64859 this waterВҰ64862 will get thirstyВҰ64864 againВҰ64865,\wj*
\v 14 \wj but whoeverВҰ64866 drinksВҰ64871 the water that I give them will find a well springing up inside themвҖ”springing into eternalВҰ64904 lifeВҰ64903.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 15 So the womanВҰ64909 said, вҖңOkay, then. Give me some of that waterВҰ64915 so that I won't get thirstyВҰ64918 and won't have to keep coming out here to the well.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 Yeshua said, вҖң\wj First, go and get yourВҰ64938 husbandВҰ64937 and then comeВҰ64940 back here.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add Actually,\add* I don't have a husband!вҖқ she \add вүҲretorted\add*.
\p вҖң\wj True enoughвҖ”indeed you don't,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* said.
\v 18 вҖң\wj You've had fiveВҰ64964 husbandsВҰ64966 and you're not married to the man you're living with, so what you said was true.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңMisterВҰ64985, I can see that you'reВҰ64990 a prophetВҰ64988,вҖқ the womanВҰ64984 \add вүҲreacted\add*.
\v 20 вҖңOurВҰ64993 ancestorsВҰ64992 worshipped on this mountainВҰ64997, butВҰ65000 youВҰ65001 Jews claim that people should only worship there in Yerushalem.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* told her, вҖң\wj You need to believeВҰ65018 that I was sent from God, womanВҰ65021, becauseВҰ65022 a day is comingВҰ65023 when everyone will be worshippingВҰ65038 him neitherВҰ65027 on this mountainВҰ65031, nor in Yerushalem.\wj*
\v 22 \wj You people in Shomron don'tВҰ65044 even know who youВҰ65045 worship, but we do, becauseВҰ65050 people will be saved by means of us Jews.\wj*
\v 23 \wj ButВҰ65060 a time is comingВҰ65058, starting even now, when the true worshippers will be worshipping the father in spiritВҰ65071 and truthВҰ65073, becauseВҰ65075 those are the ones that he is wanting to worship him.\wj*
\v 24 \wj \+nd GodВҰ65088\+nd* is spirit, and the ones worshipping him must worship in spirit and total honesty.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 25 The womanВҰ65105 said, вҖңI'm aware that the messiah is comingВҰ65110вҖ”God's chosen one. Whenever he appears, he'll teach us everything.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the messiah,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* responded. вҖң\wj Yes, he's speakingВҰ65129 to youВҰ65130!\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Disciples Rejoin Jesus
\p
\v 27 After this, hisВҰ65139 followers arrived back, andВҰ65131 they were astounded that he was speaking with a womanВҰ65145. However no one dared ask her, вҖңWhat are you afterВҰ65132?вҖқ Or to ask him, вҖңWhy are you talkingВҰ65146 with her?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 SoВҰ65162 the womanВҰ65170 left herВҰ65167 waterВҰ65166 jar there, and wentВҰ65172 back into the townВҰ65175 where she told the peopleВҰ65179,
\v 29 вҖңCome and seeВҰ65181 a manВҰ65182 who knew as much about me as I know myself! He must be the \nd messiahВҰ65195\nd*!вҖқ
\v 30 So theyВҰ65203 wentВҰ65197 out from the townВҰ65201 to go andВҰ65202 see Yeshua.
\p
\v 31 Meanwhile, Yeshua's followers encouraged him, вҖңTeacher, here, eat.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 But heВҰ65219 saidВҰ65221, вҖң\wj I've had food to eatВҰ65226 that youВҰ65228 don'tВҰ65229 know about.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 This made his followers ask each other, вҖңDid you see anyoneВҰ65242 bring himВҰ65244 somethingВҰ65244 to eatВҰ65245?вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj Obeying God who sentВҰ65259 me is like food to me, andВҰ65261 I plan to finish hisВҰ65263 workВҰ65265,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* explained.
\v 35 вҖң\wj Don't you all have a saying about needing to wait four monthsВҰ65271 for a harvest? ButВҰ65274 I'm telling you that you all should open yourВҰ65285 eyesВҰ65284 and lookВҰ65278 at the fieldsВҰ65289, becauseВҰ65290 they're alreadyВҰ65295 lightening up as harvest time approaches.\wj*
\v 36 \wj The harvester gets paid with a harvest that will last forever so that the ones who plant and the ones who harvest can all celebrate.\wj*
\v 37 \wj There's truth in the statementВҰ65325 thatВҰ65332 one person plants andВҰ65334 a different person harvests.\wj*
\v 38 \wj I've sentВҰ65339 you all out to harvest where you haven't worked beforeвҖ”othersВҰ65348 did the groundwork and you benefit from theirВҰ65356 work.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Many Samaritans Believe
\p
\v 39 And many people of ShomronВҰ65368 came out of that townВҰ65361 andВҰ65359 believedВҰ65364 that Yeshua is God becauseВҰ65369 the womanВҰ65373 had told them that he knew everything about her.
\v 40 SoВҰ65390 when they all cameВҰ65386, they asked him to stay in their town and they stayed on thereВҰ65402 for a couple of daysВҰ65404.
\p
\v 41 As a result of hisВҰ65414 teaching, many more believedВҰ65410
\v 42 so then they told the woman, вҖңWe no longerВҰ65425 believeВҰ65432 just becauseВҰ65426 of what you said, butВҰ65417 now that we've heardВҰ65436 him for ourselvesВҰ65433, we can see that he really is the saviourВҰ65448 of the worldВҰ65450.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals the official's son
\rem /s1 Jesus Returns to Galilee
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals an Official's Son
\rem /s1 Jesus the giver of life
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals the Official's Son
\p
\v 43 After his twoВҰ65456 daysВҰ65457 in Shomron \add (Samaria)\add*, Yeshua continued on up to GalileeВҰ65464.
\v 44 \x + \xo 4:44: \xt Mat 13:57; Mrk 6:4; Luk 4:24.\x*\nd HeВҰ65468\nd* himselfВҰ65465 had told them that no prophetВҰ65471 gets honouredВҰ65476 in his own home town.
\v 45 \x + \xo 4:45: \xt Yhn 2:23.\x*When he got to GalileeВҰ65485, the people accepted him, havingВҰ65492 seenВҰ65492 everything that he'd done at the feast in Yerushalem becauseВҰ65505 they had also been down there.
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals an Official's Son
\p
\v 46 \x + \xo 4:46: \xt Yhn 2:1-11.\x*SoВҰ65535 he wentВҰ65514 again to CanaВҰ65525 there in GalileeВҰ65528 whereВҰ65529 he had made the waterВҰ65533 into wine. Now there was a royalВҰ65540 officialВҰ65540 there, whoseВҰ65541 son in CapernaumВҰ65546 was ill.
\v 47 When the official heardВҰ65548 that \nd Yeshua\nd* was comingВҰ65552 up from YudeaВҰ65556 to GalileeВҰ65559, he wentВҰ65560 and asked him if he would comeВҰ65569 and healВҰ65572 hisВҰ65573 son who was dyingВҰ65578.
\v 48 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ65579 to himВҰ65584, вҖң\wj You people won'tВҰ65586 believeВҰ65594 unless you seeВҰ65591 miracles and other marvels.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 49 But the officialВҰ65600 begged himВҰ65597, вҖңSir, please comeВҰ65603 beforeВҰ65604 myВҰ65611 childВҰ65608 dies.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 вҖң\wj Go back there and see,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ65629. вҖң\wj YourВҰ65619 son will recover.\wj*вҖқ
\p The manВҰ65624 believedВҰ65622 what Yeshua had told him, and so he started off.
\v 51 On his way, his slavesВҰ65644 met him and reportedВҰ65651 that the boyВҰ65658 was alive and well.
\p
\v 52 SoВҰ65663 the official asked them what time it was that he got betterВҰ65673, and they replied that the feverВҰ65687 had subsided around 1pm.
\v 53 The fatherВҰ65691 knewВҰ65688 that that was the time when Yeshua had told him that his son would recover, and as a result his wholeВҰ65716 householdВҰ65714 believedВҰ65710 \add that Yeshua came from God\add*.
\p
\v 54 This was the secondВҰ65722 miracle that \nd Yeshua\nd* have done after leaving YudeaВҰ65731 andВҰ65719 going to GalileeВҰ65734.
\c 5
\s1 Yeshua heals a man at the pool
\rem /s1 The Healing at the Pool
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Lame Man
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ65735 all this, thereВҰ65737 was another Jewish feastВҰ65739, so \nd Yeshua\nd* wentВҰ65743 down to Yerushalem.
\v 2 In Yerushalem at the Sheep Gate, there'sВҰ65748 the BethsaidaВҰ65766 pool thatВҰ65758 has fiveВҰ65768 alcoves
\v 3 and a large number of sick, blindВҰ65780, lame, and paralysedВҰ65782 peopleВҰ65776 lie there in them.
\v 4 в—ҳ
\v 5 One manВҰ65825 had been thereВҰ65826 for thirty-eight yearsВҰ65832,
\v 6 and when \nd Yeshua\nd* noticed him and knew that he'd been there for so long, he asked, вҖң\wj Do you want to get better?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖңYes mister,вҖқ the sick man answeredВҰ65864, вҖңbutВҰ65889 when the waterВҰ65878 starts moving, I don'tВҰ65872 have a companion to lift me into the pool, so someone else always get there beforeВҰ65893 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* said, вҖң\wj Stand up and pick up yourВҰ65907 bedroll and start walkingВҰ65909.\wj*вҖқ
\v 9 The man immediatelyВҰ65911 stood up, picked up hisВҰ65925 gear, andВҰ65910 started to walkВҰ65927.
\p However, this was the weekly rest day.
\v 10 \x + \xo 5:10: \xt Neh 13:19; Jer 17:21.\x*SoВҰ65937 the religious leaders said to the man, вҖңHey! It's against the law for you to carry yourВҰ65953 beddingВҰ65952 on the rest dayВҰ65943!вҖқ
\p
\v 11 ButВҰ65974 the man answeredВҰ65957, вҖңThe man who made me better told me to pick up my bedroll andВҰ65974 start walkingВҰ65975.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңOh. Who was it that told youВҰ65986 to take that stuff andВҰ65992 start walkingВҰ65993?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 But the man who had been healedВҰ65997 didn'tВҰ65999 even know who it was, because \nd Yeshua\nd* had quickly left when a crowdВҰ66010 had formed.
\p
\v 14 Later on, \nd Yeshua\nd* found the man in the templeВҰ66027 and told him, вҖң\wj LookВҰ66032, you're better now so don't go on sinningВҰ66036, because you don't want anything worseВҰ66039 to happen to you.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 15 The manВҰ66049 then wentВҰ66045 andВҰ66050 told the leaders that it was \nd Yeshua\nd* who had made himВҰ66066 better.
\rem /s1 Life Through the Son
\rem /s1 Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God
\v 16 As a result, the leaders started harassing \nd Yeshua\nd* because he had done this on a rest dayВҰ66090.
\v 17 ButВҰ66104 Yeshua just replied, вҖң\wj MyВҰ66100 fatherВҰ66099 is working today, andВҰ66104 so I'm also working.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 18 Because of this, the leaders became determined that he must be put to deathвҖ”not just because he broke the rules for the rest dayВҰ66123, but most of all because he was callingВҰ66128 God his own fatherВҰ66126, thus makingВҰ66134 himselfВҰ66133 equalВҰ66132 to God!
\s1 Authority over life is given to the son
\rem /s1 The Authority of the Son
\p
\v 19 SoВҰ66139 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded to them, вҖң\wj I want to tell you all something: The son can'tВҰ66154 initiate anythingВҰ66173 by himselfВҰ66164. He can only do what he sees his father doing, becauseВҰ66181 whateverВҰ66180 his father is doing, he also does things like that.\wj*
\v 20 \wj You see, the fatherВҰ66197 loves his son and shows him everything that he's doingВҰ66209. In fact, he'll be showing him even greaterВҰ66212 things than what he's done already, so that you all will be amazedВҰ66222.\wj*
\v 21 \wj BecauseВҰ66227 the fatherВҰ66229 brings the dead back to life, giving them new life, so too the son can give life to anyone who he wants.\wj*
\v 22 \wj The fatherВҰ66250 won'tВҰ66246 be judgingВҰ66251 anyoneВҰ66252, butВҰ66253 has already givenВҰ66257 that task to the son,\wj*
\v 23 \wj so that the people might honour the son like they honour the father. But anyone who is not honouring the son, is also dishonouring the father who sent him.\wj*
\p
\v 24 вҖң\wj I assure you that anyone who hears myВҰ66290 messageВҰ66289 and believesВҰ66293 that I was sent by God, will live forever and will not be condemned, butВҰ66292 has moved from deathВҰ66311 into life.\wj*
\v 25 \wj I can also assure youВҰ66318 that a time is comingВҰ66320, and in fact is here already, when the deadВҰ66327 will be hearingВҰ66330 the voice of God's son and that voice will bring them back to life.\wj*
\v 26 \wj As the fatherВҰ66346 is the source of life, he gave the power of giving life to the son\wj*
\v 27 \wj and gaveВҰ66369 him the authorityВҰ66367 to be the final judgeВҰ66372, becauseВҰ66375 he is humanity's child.\wj*
\v 28 \wj Don't be surprised at this, becauseВҰ66382 a time is comingВҰ66383 when everyone in their graves will be hearingВҰ66398 hisВҰ66401 voiceВҰ66400,\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 5:29: \xt Dan 12:2.\x*\wj and the ones having done what is goodВҰ66408 will be given new lifeВҰ66412, and the ones having done what is evilВҰ66417 will be condemned.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The unbelief of the religious leaders
\rem /s1 Witnesses to Jesus
\p
\v 30 Yeshua continued explaining to the religious leaders, вҖң\wj I don'tВҰ66423 do anything in isolation. Whenever I hearВҰ66436 from him, only then do I judge and my judgementВҰ66440 is correct and impartial becauseВҰ66445 I'm not imposing \+em my\+em* desires, butВҰ66438 the desire of the one who sentВҰ66457 me.\wj*
\rem /s1 Testimonies About Jesus
\rem /s1 Witnesses to Jesus
\p
\v 31 вҖң\wj If I just testified about myselfВҰ66464, myВҰ66467 testimonyВҰ66466 would not be correct or even valid.\wj*
\v 32 \wj However it's another one that's testifying about me, and I know that his testimonyВҰ66484 about me is true.\wj*
\v 33 \x + \xo 5:33: \xt Yhn 1:19-27; 3:27-30.\x*\wj You sentВҰ66491 people out to question Yohan andВҰ66494 his testimonyВҰ66495 was true.\wj*
\v 34 \wj butВҰ66508 I don'tВҰ66500 even need any testimonyВҰ66506 that comes from people, because I am teaching youВҰ66512 how to be savedВҰ66513.\wj*
\v 35 \wj Yohan was a bright and shiningВҰ66521 lightВҰ66531 and youВҰ66522 appreciated it for a short time.\wj*
\v 36 \wj But I have a stronger testimonyВҰ66537 than Yohan's becauseВҰ66544 the father has entrusted works to me to completeВҰ66554, and which I'm already doingВҰ66562 and which clearly show thatВҰ66560 the father sent me here.\wj*
\v 37 \x + \xo 5:37: \xt Mat 3:17; Mrk 1:11; Luk 3:22.\x*\wj And since he sentВҰ66575 me, he himself has testifiedВҰ66581 about me. You people have never listened to hisВҰ66586 voiceВҰ66585, nor have you ever seenВҰ66594 him!\wj*
\v 38 \wj And hisВҰ66598 way of thinking is obviously not in your minds, becauseВҰ66605 you don'tВҰ66599 believeВҰ66613 the one that he sentВҰ66607.\wj*
\v 39 \wj You look in the Jewish scriptures becauseВҰ66617 you supposeВҰ66619 that they'll lead you to eternalВҰ66624 lifeВҰ66623. Those very scriptures testifyВҰ66633 about me coming,\wj*
\v 40 \wj yet you refuse to comeВҰ66639 to me in orderВҰ66642 to receive lifeВҰ66643.\wj*
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj I'm not getting any praise from people\wj*
\v 42 \wj but I do know that you people don'tВҰ66662 actually loveВҰ66659 \+nd GodВҰ66661\+nd* in your hearts.\wj*
\v 43 \wj I have come with myВҰ66675 father'sВҰ66674 authority and you don'tВҰ66677 accept me, butВҰ66676 if someone came claiming their own authority, you'd happily accept them.\wj*
\v 44 \wj How \+em could\+em* you possibly believeВҰ66693 when you just accept acclamations from each other, butВҰ66699 don'tВҰ66707 even seek praise from the only \+nd GodВҰ66706\+nd*.\wj*
\v 45 \wj But don't be assuming that I'llВҰ66713 be accusing you all in front of the fatherВҰ66720. No, the one who'll accuse you is Mosheh because he's the one that you're hoping to please.\wj*
\v 46 \wj The trouble is that if you actually believed what Mosheh wroteВҰ66745, you would believe me, becauseВҰ66741 Mosheh was writing about me.\wj*
\v 47 \wj But since you don'tВҰ66752 really believe his writingsВҰ66751, you're not at all likely to believe me.\wj*вҖқ
\c 6
\s1 Feeding 5,000 families
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds Five Thousand
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds the Five Thousand
\rem /s1 Feeding the Five Thousand
\rem /s1 Bread from heaven
\r (Mat. 14:13-21; Mark 6:30-44; Luke 9:10-17)
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ66762 all this, \nd Yeshua\nd* crossed the lakeВҰ66769 \add in a boat\add*.\f + \fr 6:1 \ft Here Yohan also uses the Roman name вҖңLake TiberiasвҖқ rather than just вҖңLake GalileeвҖқ.\f*
\v 2 A large crowdВҰ66781 followedВҰ66778 himВҰ66780 becauseВҰ66784 they'd seen his miraculous healings of sick people.
\v 3 \nd YeshuaВҰ66807\nd* climbed a hillВҰ66805 andВҰ66808 sat thereВҰ66809 with hisВҰ66816 apprenticesВҰ66815.
\v 4 At that time, it was getting close to the Jewish Festival of Passover.
\v 5 When \nd Yeshua\nd* looked out and saw the large crowd comingВҰ66842, he asked PhilipВҰ66848, вҖң\wj Where can we get enough food from to feed all this crowd?\wj*вҖқ
\v 6 ButВҰ66860 he was only sayingВҰ66861 this to test Philip becauseВҰ66866 he already knew what he was goingВҰ66869 to do.
\p
\v 7 Philip answeredВҰ66871, вҖңTo buy even just a snack for this many people would take several months' wages!вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Now one of Yeshua's apprenticesВҰ66895, SimonВҰ66900 Peter's brotherВҰ66899, AndrewВҰ66897, said to Yeshua,
\v 9 вҖңThere's a young boyВҰ66903 here with fiveВҰ66909 buns andВҰ66912 twoВҰ66913 \add smallВҰ66903 cooked\add* fishВҰ66914, butВҰ66915 that wouldn't even start to feed this crowd.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 ButВҰ66932 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them to get all the peopleВҰ66929 to sitВҰ66930 down as thereВҰ66931 was a large grassyВҰ66934 area. SoВҰ66932 they all satВҰ66940 downвҖ”some fiveВҰ66950 thousandВҰ66950 menВҰ66944 were counted.
\v 11 Then he took the buns and gaveВҰ66960 thanksВҰ66960 to God, and started passing around both the buns and the fishВҰ66977, and everyone ate as much as they wanted.
\v 12 Once everyone was full, Yeshua got hisВҰ66986 apprenticesВҰ66985 to collect the leftoverВҰ66989 fragmentsВҰ66991 so as not to waste anythingВҰ66994.
\v 13 SoВҰ66999 they gatheredВҰ66998 the leftovers and filledВҰ67002 twelveВҰ67006 basketsВҰ67007 with leftover bread.
\p
\v 14 The peopleВҰ67022 who had witnessed this and other miracles said, вҖңThis really is the prophetВҰ67038 that God promised to send!вҖқ
\v 15 ButВҰ67051 \nd YeshuaВҰ67045\nd* knew that they intended to come and grab him to proclaim him as their kingВҰ67059, so he moved out of the crowd and on up the hillВҰ67065.
\s1 Yeshua comes walking across the lake
\rem /s1 Jesus Walks on Water
\rem /s1 Jesus Walks on the Water
\r (Mat. 14:22-33; Mark 6:45-52)
\p
\v 16 As itВҰ67074 moved into eveningВҰ67073, Yeshua's apprenticesВҰ67077 wentВҰ67075 back down to the lakeВҰ67081
\v 17 and havingВҰ67084 boardedВҰ67084 the boatВҰ67087, theyВҰ67088 set out acrossВҰ67092 the lakeВҰ67094 toward CapernaumВҰ67096. By thenВҰ67098 it was dark, and there was still no sign of \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ67119 a strong windВҰ67122 hit the lakeВҰ67121 andВҰ67119 the water got rough.
\v 19 When they had rowedВҰ67126 aboutВҰ67130 fiveВҰ67135 kilometres, they saw \nd Yeshua\nd* walkingВҰ67141 on top of the lakeВҰ67145 and approaching the boatВҰ67150, and they were very scared.
\v 20 But he told them, вҖң\wj Don't worryвҖ”it's me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 21 After thatВҰ67186 they were willingВҰ67164 to let him into the boat, and immediatelyВҰ67174 the boat was at their arrival place.
\rem /s1 The Bread from Heaven
\rem /s1 Jesus, the Bread of Life
\rem /s1 The People Seek Jesus
\p
\v 22 The next day, the crowdВҰ67192 looked acrossВҰ67195 the lakeВҰ67197 and saw that only one smallВҰ67202 boat had crossed, and they knew that only \nd Yeshua's\nd* apprentices had boarded that boat and left, and not Yeshua himself.
\v 23 Other boatsВҰ67251 cameВҰ67249 across from TiberiasВҰ67258 near the placeВҰ67262 whereВҰ67263 theyВҰ67265 had eaten the breadВҰ67267 after the \nd masterВҰ67270\nd* had givenВҰ67268 thanksВҰ67268.
\v 24 SoВҰ67273 when all the people sawВҰ67274 that Yeshua wasn't around and hisВҰ67289 apprenticesВҰ67288 had left, they wentВҰ67303 off lookingВҰ67306 forВҰ67306 Yeshua in CapernaumВҰ67305.
\s1 The bread that enables true life
\rem /s1 Jesus the Bread of Life
\p
\v 25 WhenВҰ67309 they foundВҰ67311 him there acrossВҰ67313 the lakeВҰ67315, they queried, вҖңTeacherВҰ67318, how did you get here?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj Honestly, I know that you're not lookingВҰ67334 forВҰ67334 me because you sawВҰ67338 \+add God working\+add* miracles,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ67324, вҖң\wj butВҰ67328 because you all had plenty of food to fill you up.\wj*
\v 27 \wj Don't \+add just\+add* work for the food which goes off, butВҰ67357 for the food which lasts foreverвҖ”the food which humanity's child will give to youВҰ67371 becauseВҰ67374 \+nd GodВҰ67379\+nd* the fatherВҰ67376 has put his mark of approval on him.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 28 Puzzled, they asked himВҰ67383, вҖңWhat should we be doing if we want to work for \nd GodВҰ67396\nd*?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 He answered, вҖң\wj Doing God's workВҰ67407 is putting your trust in the one that he sentВҰ67416 here.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖңIf so,вҖқ they saidВҰ67419, вҖңwhat miracle will you do for us to seeВҰ67432 so that we can believeВҰ67434 that you \add came from God\add*? What can \em you\em* do?
\v 31 \x + \xo 6:31: \xt Exo 16:4,15; Psa 78:24.\x*OurВҰ67440 ancestorsВҰ67439 ateВҰ67443 the mannaВҰ67442\f + \fr 6:31 \ft Manna was a word that meant вҖҳstuffвҖҷ and referred to some kind of flakes that regularly came down from the sky in the time of Mosheh and could be eaten as food.\f* out in the wildernessВҰ67446, just like Mosheh wroteВҰ67449, вҖҳHe gaveВҰ67455 them breadВҰ67451 from the sky to eatВҰ67458.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 32 \nd Yeshua\nd* said to them, вҖң\wj Actually I can tell you that it wasn't Mosheh who gaveВҰ67470 them bread from heaven, but myВҰ67481 fatherВҰ67480 gives you the real bread from heaven,\wj*
\v 33 \wj becauseВҰ67493 God's breadВҰ67494 is the one who came down from heavenВҰ67503 andВҰ67504 who gives lifeВҰ67505 to the worldВҰ67510.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 34 SoВҰ67512 theyВҰ67511 requested, вҖңMisterВҰ67515, keep giving us that breadВҰ67521.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the breadВҰ67532 that gives lifeВҰ67534,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj anyone who comes to me will never hungerВҰ67541, andВҰ67544 the one believingВҰ67546 in me, will never be thirstyВҰ67551 again.\wj*
\v 36 \wj ButВҰ67563 as I saidВҰ67556 already, although you have seenВҰ67560 me you refuse to believeВҰ67565 me.\wj*
\v 37 \wj EveryoneВҰ67567 that the fatherВҰ67572 gives to me will come to me, andВҰ67576 I certainly won'tВҰ67582 turn away anyone who comes to me,\wj*
\v 38 \wj because I cameВҰ67587 down from heavenВҰ67591, not to do what I want, butВҰ67600 to do what the one who sentВҰ67604 me wants.\wj*
\v 39 \wj And what he wants is for me to not lose anyone thatВҰ67618 he's givenВҰ67619 to me, butВҰ67608 to bring them back to life on the last dayВҰ67635.\wj*
\v 40 \wj MyВҰ67648 fatherВҰ67645 wants everyoneВҰ67650 who watches me and believesВҰ67656 in me to live forever, becauseВҰ67638 I will bring them back to lifeВҰ67662 on thatВҰ67651 final dayВҰ67672.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 41 This little speech made the religious leaders grumbleВҰ67673 aboutВҰ67678 him becauseВҰ67680 he had saidВҰ67681 that he was the foodВҰ67685 that came down from heavenВҰ67690,
\v 42 as they figured out, вҖңThis is \nd Yeshua\nd* the son of Yosef andВҰ67691 so we know his parents. SoВҰ67691 how can he say that he cameВҰ67726 down from heavenВҰ67725?вҖқ
\p
\v 43 \nd Yeshua\nd* scolded them, вҖң\wj Don't be grumblingВҰ67737 to each other.\wj*
\v 44 \wj No one can join me unless the fatherВҰ67748 who sentВҰ67751 me attracts them, andВҰ67757 then I'llВҰ67757 be bringing them back to life on that final dayВҰ67765.\wj*
\v 45 \x + \xo 6:45: \xt Isa 54:13.\x*\wj The prophetsВҰ67770 wroteВҰ67767 thatВҰ67779 the people will be taughtВҰ67774 by \+nd GodВҰ67776\+nd*. And everyone who's heardВҰ67781 andВҰ67785 learntВҰ67786 from the fatherВҰ67784 comes to me.\wj*
\v 46 \wj Not that any person has seen the fatherвҖ”only the one who came from \+nd GodВҰ67806\+nd* has seen him.\wj*
\v 47 \wj I tell youВҰ67816 sincerely: anyone who believesВҰ67819 \+add in me\+add* will live forever.\wj*
\v 48 \wj \+em I am\+em* the breadВҰ67828 that gives true lifeВҰ67830.\wj*
\v 49 \wj YourВҰ67833 ancestorsВҰ67832 ateВҰ67834 mannaВҰ67843 in the wildernessВҰ67841, butВҰ67844 theyВҰ67845 all went on to die.\wj*
\v 50 \wj ButВҰ67863 \+em I am\+em* the breadВҰ67849 thatВҰ67850 came down from heavenВҰ67853 andВҰ67863 anyoneВҰ67858 who eats this will not dieВҰ67866.\wj*
\v 51 \wj \+em I am\+em* the living bread thatВҰ67872 came down from heavenВҰ67877 and if anyoneВҰ67881 eats this bread, he will live through to the next age.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 52 At this point, the religious leaders began to argue with each other, вҖңHow could this man giveВҰ67932 us hisВҰ67937 fleshВҰ67935 to eatВҰ67938?вҖқ
\p
\v 53 SoВҰ67940 \nd Yeshua\nd* explained, вҖң\wj Indeed if you don'tВҰ67950 eatВҰ67952 my fleshВҰ67954 and drinkВҰ67960 my bloodВҰ67964, you aren'tВҰ67950 trulyВҰ67945 alive!\wj*
\v 54 \wj Anyone who eats my fleshВҰ67981 and drinksВҰ67983 my bloodВҰ67987 will gain eternalВҰ67990 lifeвҖ”I will bring them back to life on that final dayВҰ67999,\wj*
\v 55 \wj becauseВҰ68001 my fleshВҰ68002 is the true food, andВҰ68008 my bloodВҰ68010 is the true drinkВҰ68015.\wj*
\v 56 \wj Anyone who eats my fleshВҰ68054 and drinksВҰ68056 my bloodВҰ68060 lives in me, and I will live in himВҰ68066.\wj*
\v 57 \wj The father is alive and sent me here, and I am alive because of Him, so also the person who eats me will be alive because of me.\wj*
\v 58 \wj Unlike your ancestorsВҰ68137 who ate that bread \+add from the sky\+add* and then died, anyone who eats this bread that came down from heavenВҰ68130 will live through to the next age.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Many people find the teaching too difficult
\p
\v 59 Yeshua taughtВҰ68162 all of this in the meetingВҰ68160 hallВҰ68160 there in CapernaumВҰ68164.
\rem /s1 Many Disciples Desert Jesus
\rem /s1 The Words of Eternal Life
\v 60 But even many of hisВҰ68172 followers who heardВҰ68168 it saidВҰ68174, вҖңThis is difficult teachingвҖ”it's too hard to take.вҖқ
\p
\v 61 But \nd Yeshua\nd* already knew inside that hisВҰ68204 followers were grumblingВҰ68199 aboutВҰ68200 this and asked them, вҖң\wj Do youВҰ68210 find this offensiveВҰ68211?\wj*
\v 62 \wj WhatВҰ68221 if you were to see humanity's child ascending to whereВҰ68224 he came from?\wj*
\v 63 \wj It's the spirit that is the source of life, not the bodyВҰ68234. The concepts that I'veВҰ68243 taught you are all spiritual and life-giving.\wj*
\v 64 \wj ButВҰ68277 thereВҰ68253 are some here who don'tВҰ68261 believe me.\wj*вҖқ Actually, \nd Yeshua\nd* had already knownВҰ68264 from the beginningВҰ68268 just who would believe andВҰ68277 which person would betray himВҰ68285
\v 65 so he saidВҰ68291, вҖң\wj That's why I told you that no one can comeВҰ68296 to me unless the fatherВҰ68307 has givenВҰ68303 them to me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 66 After this, many of hisВҰ68317 followers wentВҰ68318 back and no longerВҰ68323 accompanied him around.
\p
\v 67 SoВҰ68329 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ68327 to his twelveВҰ68333 \add apprentices\add*, вҖң\wj Don't you want to leave as well?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 68 \x + \xo 6:68-69: \xt Mat 16:16; Mrk 8:29; Luk 9:20.\x*вҖң\nd MasterВҰ68346\nd*,вҖқ Simon answeredВҰ68339, вҖңif we went, who would we follow then? You're the \add only\add* one who teaches about living forever.
\v 69 We believeВҰ68356 andВҰ68357 know that youВҰ68361 are the holy son of \nd GodВҰ68369\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 70 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj Didn't I choose all twelveВҰ68386 of you myself? And yet one of you is a devilВҰ68394.\wj*вҖқ
\v 71 (He was talkingВҰ68396 about YudasВҰ68399, SimonВҰ68400 Iscariot's son, becauseВҰ68405 he was the one who would go on to betray him.)
\c 7
\s1 Yeshua's sceptical brothers dare him to go public
\rem /s1 Jesus Goes to the Feast of Tabernacles; The Unbelief of Jesus' Brothers; Jesus and His Brothers; The great controversy
\p
\v 1 After all this, \nd Yeshua\nd* travelled around GalileeВҰ68427. (He didn'tВҰ68428 want to travel around YudeaВҰ68435 becauseВҰ68429 the leaders there wanted to execute himВҰ68439.)
\v 2 \x + \xo 7:2: \xt Lev 23:34; Deu 16:13.\x*As itВҰ68443 was now getting close to the Jewish Feast With Tents,
\v 3 hisВҰ68459 brothersВҰ68458 saidВҰ68453 to him, вҖңYou should leave this place and go down to YudeaВҰ68469 so that all yourВҰ68474 followers can see the miracles that you'reВҰ68484 doingВҰ68484.
\v 4 If you want to become well-known, you don't do things out of the main stream. If you want to do miracles, \add go and\add* show yourselfВҰ68505 to the wider worldВҰ68507.
\v 5 (You see, not even Yeshua's own \add half-\add*brothers believedВҰ68514 \add that he came from God\add*.)
\p
\v 6 SoВҰ68520 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj Well, you guys can do that any time, but it's not the right time for me yet.\wj*
\v 7 \wj All the people won'tВҰ68541 hate youВҰ68548 guys, butВҰ68550 they do hate me becauseВҰ68552 I teach about the evilВҰ68562 things they are doing.\wj*
\v 8 \wj You all goВҰ68565 on down to Yerushalem ahead of me. I'm not goingВҰ68573 to the feast yet becauseВҰ68578 it's not yet the right timeВҰ68583 for me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 9 After saying this, Yeshua stayed up in GalileeВҰ68598.
\s1 Yeshua starts teaching about authentic justice
\rem /s1 Jesus at the Festival of Booths; Jesus at the Festival of Shelters; Jesus Teaches Openly at the Temple
\p
\v 10 But after hisВҰ68605 \add half-\add*brothers had left to go down to Yerushalem, Yeshua also wentвҖ”not in the public limelight butВҰ68601 just incognito so to speak.
\v 11 However at the celebrations, the Jewish religious leaders were searching for him, and were asking around where he was.
\p
\v 12 Even amongВҰ68643 the crowdsВҰ68646 thereВҰ68641 was a lot of quiet banter with some saying that Yeshua is a good man andВҰ68635 othersВҰ68655 complaining that he was misleading the people.
\v 13 Either way, no one was speakingВҰ68667 out in publicВҰ68666 about himВҰ68670, becauseВҰ68672 they were afraid of the reaction of the religious leaders.
\rem /s1 Jesus Teaches at the Feast
\p
\v 14 Finally sometime in the middleВҰ68681 of the celebrations, \nd Yeshua\nd* wentВҰ68682 into the templeВҰ68688 andВҰ68689 started teachingВҰ68690 in there.
\v 15 Even the Jewish leaders were surprised, asking, вҖңHow can this man know so much when he hasn't been trained as a teacher?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \nd Yeshua\nd* himself respondedВҰ68709, вҖң\wj My teachingВҰ68712 doesn't come from me, butВҰ68716 from the one who sentВҰ68718 me.\wj*
\v 17 \wj If anyoneВҰ68721 wants to do God's will, they'll soon figure out whetherВҰ68732 my teachingВҰ68731 comes from God or if I'm just making itВҰ68737 up myselfВҰ68741.\wj*
\v 18 \wj Any person who just teaches their own thoughts is just seeking their own advancement, butВҰ68754 anyone who wants to promote the one who sentВҰ68759 them, this is authentic andВҰ68764 there's no hidden self-interest.\wj*
\v 19 \wj Didn't Mosheh write down God's commands for you, yet not a single one of you obeys them. Why are you wanting to execute me?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңYou must be demon-possessed,вҖқ said some in the crowdВҰ68791, вҖңWho would be wanting to execute youВҰ68797.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ68805, вҖң\wj I did one miracle and youВҰ68813 were all amazedВҰ68813.\wj*
\v 22 \x + \xo 7:22: a \xt Lev 12:3; \xo b \xt Gen 17:10.\x*\wj Mosheh gaveВҰ68818 you the command about circumcision (even though it actually came from before his time), butВҰ68835 to obey this, you'll even circumcise a baby boy on the Rest Day.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 7:23: \xt Yhn 5:9.\x*\wj So if a \+add baby\+add* boy can be circumcisedВҰ68842 on the Rest Day so that Mosheh's commands aren'tВҰ68849 brokenВҰ68850, they why did you get angryВҰ68857 with me becauseВҰ68858 I made a man healthyВҰ68862 on the Rest Day?\wj*
\v 24 \wj Don't just вҖҳjudgeвҖҷ things so that you yourselves look good, butВҰ68871 judge impartially, seeking the best for others.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Could Yeshua be the messiah?
\rem /s1 Is Jesus the Christ?
\rem /s1 Is This the Christ?
\rem /s1 Is He the Messiah?
\rem /s1 Is Jesus the Messiah?
\p
\v 25 After this, some of the locals from Yerushalem started asking, вҖңIsn't this the man theyВҰ68887 were wanting to execute?
\v 26 Well, here he is teaching in publicВҰ68891, yet they're not even confronting him. PerhapsВҰ68899 the leaders know that he really is the \nd messiahВҰ68911\nd*?
\v 27 But weВҰ68914 even know where this man is from. Surely when the \nd messiahВҰ68920\nd* comes, no one would know his family background.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 SoВҰ68938 as \nd Yeshua\nd* continued teachingВҰ68946, he called out, вҖң\wj Indeed you all know me and my home and my family. ButВҰ68950 I didn'tВҰ68963 comeВҰ68964 here of my own accord, butВҰ68950 the one who sentВҰ68970 me here is truthful, even though you don'tВҰ68963 even know him.\wj*
\v 29 \wj I know him, becauseВҰ68980 I came from him, indeed, he was the one who sentВҰ68987 me here.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 30 SoВҰ68992 now they really want to arrestВҰ68994 him, but no one touched him becauseВҰ69006 it was not yet the proper time.
\v 31 Many in the crowdВҰ69020 did believeВҰ69023 thatВҰ69039 he was from God and they were sayingВҰ69027, вҖңWhen the \nd messiahВҰ69030\nd* comes, would he be doingВҰ69038 greater miracles than what we've seen this manВҰ69040 do?вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua discusses leaving as they aim to arrest him
\rem /s1 Guards Are Sent to Arrest Jesus
\rem /s1 Officers Are Sent to Arrest Jesus
\p
\v 32 The Pharisee party heardВҰ69043 the crowdВҰ69048 muttering about theseВҰ69053 things and sentВҰ69055 out some of their servants along with the chiefВҰ69059 priestsВҰ69059 to go and arrestВҰ69067 Yeshua.
\v 33 SoВҰ69070 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ69069, вҖң\wj I'll only be with youВҰ69080 all for a short while longer andВҰ69082 then I'll be goingВҰ69083 to the one who sentВҰ69086 me.\wj*
\v 34 \wj You'll look for me butВҰ69091 won'tВҰ69092 be able to find me, and you can'tВҰ69092 go whereВҰ69096 I'll be going.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 The leaders wondered, вҖңWhereВҰ69110 could he be going that we wouldn't be able to find him? Will he go and live with the Jews living out there among the Greeks and start teachingВҰ69130 the Greeks?
\v 36 And what does he mean about lookingВҰ69145 forВҰ69145 him and not being able to find him, and not being able to go whereВҰ69152 he goes?вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua offers living water to the crowd
\rem /s1 Rivers of Living Water
\rem /s1 Jesus Promises Living Water
\rem /s1 Streams of Life-Giving Water
\p
\v 37 \x + \xo 7:37: \xt Lev 23:36.\x*On the final climax dayВҰ69163 of the celebrations, \nd Yeshua\nd* stoodВҰ69172 there and shouted, вҖң\wj Anyone who's thirstyВҰ69182, come here to me and drinkВҰ69187.\wj*
\v 38 \x + \xo 7:38: \xt Eze 47:1; Zech 14:8.\x*\wj WhoeverВҰ69196 trusts me will have rivers of livingВҰ69203 waterВҰ69202 flowingВҰ69201 out from himВҰ69200 just like the scripturesВҰ69195 say.\wj*вҖқ
\v 39 He was talking about God's spirit that the ones who trust him would receiveВҰ69214 in the futureвҖ”not yet becauseВҰ69223 \nd Yeshua\nd* hadn't been lifted up to heaven yet.
\s1 The people are divided about Yeshua
\rem /s1 Division and Unbelief
\rem /s1 Division among the People
\p
\v 40 When some in the crowdВҰ69242 heardВҰ69246 his teaching, theyВҰ69254 said, вҖңHe really is the \add coming\add* prophetВҰ69261.вҖқ
\v 41 OthersВҰ69262 said, вҖңHe must be the messiah.вҖқ
\p But some pointed out, вҖңThe messiah won'tВҰ69274 come from GalileeВҰ69278.
\v 42 \x + \xo 7:42: \xt 2Sam 7:12; Mic 5:2.\x*Don't the scripturesВҰ69285 say that he'll be a descendant of King David andВҰ69293 that he'll come from David's town of BethlehemВҰ69295?вҖқ
\v 43 And so the crowdВҰ69316 was divided about Yeshua.
\v 44 Some \add of the Pharisees' servants\add* wanted to arrestВҰ69327 him, butВҰ69322 decided to leave him alone \add for now\add*.
\s1 The leaders distrust Yeshua and mock his followers
\rem /s1 Unbelief of the Jewish Leaders; The Unbelief of Those in Authority; The Unbelief of the Jewish Authorities
\p
\v 45 SoВҰ69341 when the servants returned back to the chiefВҰ69346 priestsВҰ69346 and the Pharisees, they were asked, вҖңWhy haven't youВҰ69357 broughtВҰ69357 himВҰ69360?вҖқ
\p
\v 46 They answeredВҰ69361, вҖңWe've neverВҰ69368 heard anyone speak like he does.вҖқ
\p
\v 47 вҖңDon't tell us that you've also been taken in by him?вҖқ the Pharisees asked them.
\v 48 вҖңNone of our leaders or any of us Pharisees believeВҰ69394 that he's from God.
\v 49 But all these people ignorant of the scriptures are bewitched.вҖқ
\p
\v 50 \x + \xo 7:50: \xt Yhn 3:1-2.\x*Now Nicodemus (the one who had previously visited Yeshua) spoke up,
\v 51 вҖңSince when did ourВҰ69442 rules allow us to judge a personВҰ69445 before we've even heard them out andВҰ69453 investigated what they're doingВҰ69457?вҖқ
\p
\v 52 вҖңSo do you come from Galilee as well?вҖқ they sneered, вҖңLook in the scriptures and you'll soon seeВҰ69475 that no prophetВҰ69484 emerges out of \em Galilee\em*.вҖқ
\rem The story of the woman caught in adultery does not appear in the majority of the oldest manuscripts that we have. Hence, it is not included in this translation.
\rem (That doesn't necessarily mean that the event never happenedвҖ”just that it almost certainly wasn't part of Yohan's original account.)
