\s1 The two witnesses of Yeshua's authenticity
\rem /s1 Jesus, the Light of the World; The Validity of Jesus' Testimony
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 8:12: \xt Mat 5:14; Yhn 9:5.\x*Because of this, \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the light for the worldВҰ69754вҖ”whoever followsВҰ69756 me won'tВҰ69759 walk in the darknessВҰ69764 but will have the light \+add that gives\+add* lifeВҰ69771.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 8:13: \xt Yhn 5:31.\x*Some from the Pharisee partyВҰ69776 argued, вҖңYou are testifyingВҰ69780 aboutВҰ69778 yourselfВҰ69779, so that testimonyВҰ69782 is invalid.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ69791, вҖң\wj Even when I am testifying aboutВҰ69798 myselfВҰ69799, myВҰ69806 testimonyВҰ69805 is valid, becauseВҰ69809 I know where I cameВҰ69812 from and where I'm going.\wj*
\v 15 \wj You all are judging accordingВҰ69827 to your earthly values. I'm not judging anyoneВҰ69836.\wj*
\v 16 \wj ButВҰ69857 even if I was judging, my judgementВҰ69844 would be correct, becauseВҰ69850 it wouldn't just be me judging, butВҰ69857 also the fatherВҰ69861 who sent me.\wj*
\v 17 \x + \xo 8:17: \xt Deu 19:15.\x*\wj It's even writtenВҰ69869 in yourВҰ69868 own laws that the testimonyВҰ69876 of twoВҰ69873 menВҰ69874 is valid.\wj*
\v 18 \wj So that's me testifying about myselfВҰ69885, plusВҰ69886 the fatherВҰ69894 who sentВҰ69892 me also testifies about me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңAnd where is yourВҰ69902 father?вҖқ they asked.
\p \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ69903 them, вҖң\wj You don't know either me or my father. If you did know me, then you'd also know my father.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 He explained all this while he was teachingВҰ69938 in the treasuryВҰ69937 part of the templeВҰ69941, butВҰ69942 no one arrestedВҰ69944 him becauseВҰ69946 the time for hisВҰ69951 \add suffering\add* had not yet arrived.
\s1 You can't go where I'm going
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Death
\rem /s1 You Cannot Go Where I Am Going
\rem /s1 The Unbelieving People Warned
\p
\v 21 SoВҰ69954 he continuedВҰ69952, вҖң\wj I will be going away and all of you will be lookingВҰ69962 forВҰ69962 me, butВҰ69961 you'll all just die in yourВҰ69970 sins and won'tВҰ69976 be able to go whereВҰ69972 I'll be going.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 This puzzled the Jewish teachers, вҖңSurelyВҰ69983 he's not going to commit suicide! What else could he mean about вҖҳyou can'tВҰ69983 go where I'm going to be goingвҖҷ?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 Yeshua explained, вҖң\wj All of youВҰ70013 are from the world belowВҰ70005, but I'm from the world aboveВҰ70011. You all are part of this world, but I'm not part of it.\wj*
\v 24 \wj That's why I said that you'll be dying in your sins, becauseВҰ70038 if you refuse to believeВҰ70040 that I am \+add God\+add*, you will indeed all be dying in your sins.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңSoВҰ70054 who are you?вҖқ they asked.
\p And he answered, вҖң\wj Still just the same as I've been telling you from the beginningВҰ70068.\wj*
\v 26 \wj I have a lot that I need to tell youВҰ70079 all and to judge many of your actions, because the one who sentВҰ70086 me is true, and it's what I hear from himВҰ70096 that I speak to all people.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 (They didn'tВҰ70104 realise that he was talkingВҰ70111 to them aboutВҰ70107 the fatherВҰ70108 \add in heaven\add*.)
\v 28 SoВҰ70116 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj When you all lift up\wj*\f + \fr 8:28 \ft lifted up / exalted: There's a play on words here. See https://bibleDifferences.net/2019/04/25/156-exulted (dead link???)\f* \wj humanity's child \+add on a pole\+add*, then you will know that I am \+add God\+add*, and that I don't do anything by myselfВҰ70137, butВҰ70135 I say all this just as the fatherВҰ70149 told me to.\wj*
\v 29 \wj And the one who sentВҰ70156 me is with meвҖ”he didn'tВҰ70161 just leave me aloneВҰ70164вҖ”becauseВҰ70170 I am continually doingВҰ70175 what pleasesВҰ70173 him.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 30 After he'd said all this, many people believedВҰ70181 in him.
\s1 Yeshua teaches about freedom from slavery
\rem /s1 The Children of Abraham
\rem /s1 Jesus and Abraham
\rem /s1 True Disciples
\rem /s1 The Truth Will Set You Free
\p
\v 31 Because of this, \nd Yeshua\nd* told all the Jews who believedВҰ70190 in himВҰ70191, вҖң\wj If you all continue to believe my messageВҰ70199, then you're my true followers.\wj*
\v 32 \wj You will have known the truth, andВҰ70207 the truth will set you free.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 8:33: \xt Mat 3:9; Luk 3:8.\x*ButВҰ70225 some queried, вҖңWe are Abraham's descendants andВҰ70225 we've never been slaves to anyoneВҰ70227, so how can youВҰ70233 say that we'll be set free?вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj I can assure you all thatВҰ70250 anyone who sins is a slaveВҰ70254 to sin,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ70239.
\v 35 вҖң\wj And the slavesВҰ70260 don'tВҰ70261 necessarily remain in the \+add family\+add* home foreverвҖ”only the children have that right.\wj*
\v 36 \wj SoВҰ70280 if the son sets you free, then you'll be truly free.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua spars with the Jewish religious leaders
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj Yes, I know that you're all descendants of AbrahamВҰ70295, but you're trying to killВҰ70300 me becauseВҰ70302 my messageВҰ70304 doesn't lodge in you.\wj*
\v 38 \wj Indeed I talk about what I'veВҰ70312 actually seen with the father, but you all are doingВҰ70339 what you've heardВҰ70330 from your father.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Jesus and Abraham
\p
\v 39 ButВҰ70342 they retorted, вҖңAbraham is ourВҰ70347 father.вҖқ\f + \fr 8:39 \ft father meaning ancestor. (Abraham lived some 2,000 years before the time of these events.)\f*
\p And \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ70343, вҖң\wj Well, if you really were descendants of AbrahamВҰ70348, you'd behave more like himВҰ70344.\wj*
\v 40 \wj But instead you're trying to find a way to have me killedвҖ”to kill the manВҰ70375 who has spokenВҰ70380 the truth to youвҖ”truth that I heardВҰ70384 from \+nd GodВҰ70388\+nd*. AbrahamВҰ70390 never did that.\wj*
\v 41 \wj You're doingВҰ70395 what \+em yourВҰ70400\+em* father wants you all do to.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Children of the Devil
\p But they shot back, вҖңIt's not us who was conceived by a couple that weren't even married! Anyway, we only have one father and that's \nd GodВҰ70416\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 42 вҖң\wj If God was yourВҰ70429 fatherВҰ70427 you all wouldВҰ70432 be lovingВҰ70431 me,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ70417, вҖң\wj because I cameВҰ70440 from God and for God. I didn'tВҰ70444 just comeВҰ70450 by myselfВҰ70448, butВҰ70442 God sentВҰ70455 me here.\wj*
\v 43 \wj Why can't you comprehend what I'm saying? The reasonВҰ70457 that you can't stand listening to my messageВҰ70471\wj*
\v 44 \wj is because you come from your father, the devilВҰ70479, and you want to do what \+em your\+em* father wants. ButВҰ70481 he was a murdererВҰ70490 from the beginningВҰ70493, and doesn't stick to the truth because there's no truth in him. WheneverВҰ70508 he tells lies, he's speaking from his own nature, because he's a liar and the source of lying.\wj*
\v 45 \wj But becauseВҰ70525 I'm speakingВҰ70528 the truthВҰ70527, youВҰ70532 don'tВҰ70531 believeВҰ70532 in me.\wj*
\v 46 \wj WhichВҰ70535 of you can scold me for my sins? If I am speakingВҰ70546 the truthВҰ70545, why don'tВҰ70550 you believeВҰ70551 I'm from God?\wj*
\v 47 \wj Anyone who belongs to God, listens to what God says. But you all can'tВҰ70566 even hearВҰ70562 the messageВҰ70559, because you don'tВҰ70566 belong to God.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua preceded, and is greater than, Abraham
\rem /s1 Jesus and Abraham
\rem /s1 The Claims of Jesus About Himself
\p
\v 48 The Jewish leaders asked, вҖңAren't we rightВҰ70582 in sayingВҰ70583 that you'reВҰ70590 from ShomronВҰ70588 \add (SamariaВҰ70588)\add* and that you have a demonВҰ70592?вҖқ
\p
\v 49 вҖң\wj No, I don'tВҰ70601 have a demonВҰ70600,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ70594, вҖң\wj butВҰ70603 I honourВҰ70604 myВҰ70608 fatherВҰ70607 andВҰ70609 you're dishonouringВҰ70611 me.\wj*
\v 50 \wj ButВҰ70623 I'm not searching greatness for myselfвҖ”myВҰ70619 father is the one searching andВҰ70623 the one judgingВҰ70624.\wj*
\v 51 \wj I can assure youВҰ70628, that anyoneВҰ70632 who puts my teaching into practice can be certain to avoid deathВҰ70640 in \+add this\+add* age.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 52 вҖңNow we \em know\em* that you have a demonВҰ70657!вҖқ the Jews saidВҰ70649. вҖңAbrahamВҰ70659 and the prophetsВҰ70663 all diedВҰ70660, butВҰ70661 you'reВҰ70658 sayingВҰ70666 that those who follow your teaching can be certain to avoid deathВҰ70683 in \add this\add* age.
\v 53 How could you be greaterВҰ70689 than ourВҰ70693 ancestor AbrahamВҰ70694 who died? Even the prophetsВҰ70700 died. Who do you think you are?вҖқ
\p
\v 54 Again \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ70706, вҖң\wj If I praise myselfВҰ70713, my praise is worthless, but it's my fatherВҰ70721 who praises meвҖ”the one who youВҰ70727 say is your \+nd GodВҰ70731\+nd*\wj*
\v 55 \wj although in fact you don'tВҰ70736 even know him. But I have known him, and so I can'tВҰ70736 say that I haven't known him or I'd be a liar like all of you. But I have known him and I am putting hisВҰ70765 desires into practice.\wj*
\v 56 \wj YourВҰ70770 ancestor Abraham would have been excited to see me hereвҖ”in fact he did see ahead and was very happy about it.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 57 Because of that, the Jewish leaders asked, вҖңYou aren'tВҰ70792 even fiftyВҰ70789 years old yet. How could you have seenВҰ70796 Abraham?вҖқ\f + \fr 8:57 \ft Abraham lived some 2,000 years before Yeshua.\f*
\p
\v 58 \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj I can assure youВҰ70807 that \+em I am\+em*\wj*\f + \fr 8:58 \ft This awkward English is necessary to catch the play on words, because вҖҳI amвҖҷ is the meaning of God's name \+em Yahweh\+em*.\f* \wj beforeВҰ70808 AbrahamВҰ70809 ever existed.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 59 When they heard that, they picked up rocksВҰ70816 to throwВҰ70818 at Yeshua \add to kill himВҰ70820\add*. ButВҰ70824 Yeshua became hiddenВҰ70823 from their sight, and wentВҰ70825 on out of the templeВҰ70828.
\c 9
\s1 A blind man obeys and then can see
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Man Born Blind
\rem /s1 Seeing and believing
\rem /s1 A Man Born Blind Receives Sight
\p
\v 1 As Yeshua was walking along, heВҰ70840 sawВҰ70840 a manВҰ70841 who had been blindВҰ70842 from birthВҰ70844
\v 2 andВҰ70846 his followers askedВҰ70847 him, вҖңHonoured teacher, why was this manВҰ70856 born blindВҰ70863? Was it because he himself sinnedВҰ70855, or his parentsВҰ70860?вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ70866, вҖң\wj It wasn't either this manВҰ70870 or hisВҰ70875 parentsВҰ70874 that sinnedВҰ70871.\wj*\f + \fr 9:3 \ft We just want to alert our readers here that we have divided the Greek sentences here in a way that's different from the long-standing tradition. (The Greek originals have no punctuation, so either way is valid.)\f* \wj But so that \+nd GodВҰ70882\+nd* can work in him for others to see,\wj*
\v 4 \wj as long as it's daytime, we need to do what the one who sentВҰ70894 us wants, but when nighttimeВҰ70902 comes, no one will be able to work.\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 9:5: \xt Mat 5:14; Yhn 8:12.\x*\wj As long as I'm here in this world, I am the lightВҰ70914 of the world.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 6 After he'd saidВҰ70919 this, Yeshua spat on the groundВҰ70921 and after mixing some clay into a slurry, he spreadВҰ70929 it on the eyesВҰ70938 of the man
\v 7 and told himВҰ70944 to go and wash in the Siloam Pool.\f + \fr 9:7 \ft Siloam means вҖҳto be sent outвҖҷ.\f*
\p
\v 8 Then the neighboursВҰ70967 of the man and others who had seen him earlierВҰ70974, knowing that he was a beggarВҰ70976 asked, вҖңIsn't he the one who always sat and begged here?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 And indeed, some were saying, вҖңYes, this is him.вҖқ But othersВҰ70992 were saying, вҖңNo, but he looks quite similarВҰ70999.вҖқ
\p And the man said, вҖңI \em am\em* him.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 SoВҰ71010 theyВҰ71008 asked himВҰ71013, вҖңWell, how come that now youВҰ71018 can see?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңA man named \nd Yeshua\nd* made a slurry,вҖқ he said, вҖңand spreadВҰ71033 it on my eyes and told me to go and wash at SiloamВҰ71047 Pool. So I went and did it, and when I washedВҰ71056 my eyes, I could see.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 вҖңWhereВҰ71066 is he now?вҖқ theyВҰ71063 asked.
\rem /s1 The Pharisees Investigate the Healing
\p вҖңI don'tВҰ71071 know,вҖқ saidВҰ71063 the man.
\s1 The Pharisees can't accept the healing of the blind man
\p
\v 13 Then they brought the manВҰ71081 who had been blindВҰ71081 to the Pharisees.
\v 14 Now, itВҰ71082 had been the Rest Day when \nd Yeshua\nd* had made the slurry andВҰ71095 enabled himВҰ71097 to see,
\v 15 and because of this, some in the Pharisee partyВҰ71107 asked him how it was that now he could see. And he answered, вҖңWell, he put a slurry on myВҰ71118 eyesВҰ71122 and when I washedВҰ71125 them, I could see.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңWell clearly that man is not from \nd GodВҰ71142\nd*,вҖқ some of them said, вҖңbecauseВҰ71145 he doesn't respect the Rest Day.вҖқ
\p However others said, вҖңButВҰ71161 if he's just a sinner, how could he do miracles like that?вҖқ
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ71188 they asked the man who had been blindВҰ71171, вҖңWell, what do \em you\em* have to say becauseВҰ71182 it was yourВҰ71184 eyesВҰ71186 that he openedВҰ71183?вҖқ
\p вҖңHe must be a prophetВҰ71191,вҖқ the man said.
\p
\v 18 ButВҰ71204 some of the Jews weren't even sure thatВҰ71207 he really had been blindВҰ71203 before and could now see, so they calledВҰ71209 for hisВҰ71214 parentsВҰ71213
\v 19 and askedВҰ71219 them, вҖңYou two say that this is yourВҰ71229 son and that he was born blindВҰ71234. If so, how come that now he can see?вҖқ
\p
\v 20 HisВҰ71249 parentsВҰ71248 answeredВҰ71243, вҖңWe know that he's ourВҰ71258 son, and we know that he was born blindВҰ71261.
\v 21 But as for how come he can now see, we don'tВҰ71268 know that. Nor do we know who healed hisВҰ71273 eyesВҰ71276. But askВҰ71287 himвҖ”he's old enough to speakВҰ71292 for himselfВҰ71291.вҖқ
\v 22 (HisВҰ71297 parents said theseВҰ71293 things because they were afraid of the Jewish religious leaders, because the leaders had alreadyВҰ71302 announced that anyoneВҰ71311 who said that Yeshua was the \nd messiahВҰ71315\nd* would get banned from all religious ceremonies,
\v 23 so that's why they had saidВҰ71324, вҖңHe's old enoughвҖ”just askВҰ71330 him.вҖқ)
\p
\v 24 SoВҰ71334 the leaders summoned the man born blindВҰ71344 a secondВҰ71339 time and commanded him, вҖңOnly praise \nd GodВҰ71351\nd* himself for this, because we know that that man is a sinnerВҰ71360.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңWell, I don'tВҰ71370 know whether or not he's a sinnerВҰ71368,вҖқ replied the man. вҖңAll I know is that I used to be blindВҰ71376 but now I can see.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңWhat did he do to you?вҖқ they asked again. вҖңHow did he open yourВҰ71394 eyesВҰ71396?вҖқ
\p
\v 27 And he answeredВҰ71401, вҖңI alreadyВҰ71405 told you that, and you didn'tВҰ71407 even listen. Why do you want to hearВҰ71414 it all over againВҰ71411? Do you guys all want to becomeВҰ71423 hisВҰ71420 followers as well?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ71425 theyВҰ71427 insultedВҰ71427 himВҰ71429 andВҰ71430 saidВҰ71431, вҖң\em You\em* might be a follower of that man, butВҰ71440 \em weВҰ71438\em* are followers of Mosheh.
\v 29 We know that \nd GodВҰ71453\nd* spokeВҰ71450 to Mosheh, butВҰ71461 weВҰ71463 don'tВҰ71462 even know whereВҰ71464 this other fellow is from.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖңWow, that's pretty amazing,вҖқ the man respondedВҰ71471. вҖңThat man openedВҰ71490 up myВҰ71491 eyesВҰ71493, and you teachers don'tВҰ71485 even know whereВҰ71487 he's from!
\v 31 We know that \nd GodВҰ71499\nd* doesn't listen to sinnersВҰ71497, butВҰ71509 he listens to those who worship him and do what he wants.
\v 32 In all the centuries past we never heardВҰ71520 that a person could give sight to someone who was born blindВҰ71526.
\v 33 If this manВҰ71532 isn'tВҰ71538 from \nd GodВҰ71534\nd*, surely heВҰ71539 wouldn't be able to do that!вҖқ
\p
\v 34 They reacted, вҖңYou're just an ignorant sinner, andВҰ71560 you think you can teachВҰ71558 \em us\em*!вҖқ ThenВҰ71560 they had him thrownВҰ71561 out of the room.
\s1 Spiritual blindness and hypocrisy
\rem /s1 Spiritual Blindness
\p
\v 35 \nd Yeshua\nd* heardВҰ71565 that they had thrownВҰ71570 out the man who could now see, and when he foundВҰ71574 him, he saidВҰ71578, вҖң\wj Do you believeВҰ71581 that humanity's child \+add came from God\+add*?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 36 And the man answeredВҰ71588, вҖңMister, who is he so that I can believeВҰ71599 in him?вҖқ
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj You've seenВҰ71610 him and heard him and he's speakingВҰ71614 to you right now,\wj*вҖқ said \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\p
\v 38 вҖңI do believeВҰ71624, \nd masterВҰ71625\nd*,вҖқ the man responded. ThenВҰ71622 he knelt down in front of Yeshua.
\p
\v 39 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ71631, вҖң\wj I cameВҰ71643 into this worldВҰ71641 to dispense judgementВҰ71636, so that the people who can'tВҰ71647 see will be able to see, andВҰ71650 so that the ones who can see will becomeВҰ71655 blindВҰ71654.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 40 The Pharisees with him heardВҰ71657 that and asked, вҖңAre you saying that we're blindВҰ71675?вҖқ
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj If you were blindВҰ71684,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj you wouldn't be sinning, but since you all declare that you can see, then yourВҰ71704 sin remainsВҰ71705.\wj*
\c 10
\s1 The sheep know their true carer
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Shepherd
\rem /s1 The Good Shepherd and His Sheep
\rem /s1 Jesus the Good Shepherd
\rem /s1 Victory over death
\rem /s1 The Shepherd and His Flock
\p
\v 1 вҖң\wj Honestly I can tell youВҰ71710: It's not the person that enters the sheepВҰ71722 enclosure by the gate that is a thiefВҰ71728 andВҰ71730 robberВҰ71731, butВҰ71723 rather the one who climbs in a different wayВҰ71725.\wj*
\v 2 \wj The one that comes in the gate is the shepherdВҰ71741 of the sheepВҰ71746.\wj*
\v 3 \wj The gatekeeper opens up for him, and when he calls the sheep by nameВҰ71768 they listen to hisВҰ71756 voiceВҰ71755 and he leads them out.\wj*
\v 4 \wj WheneverВҰ71773 he moves the sheep, he goes in front and the sheep followВҰ71787 him becauseВҰ71788 they recognise hisВҰ71793 voiceВҰ71792.\wj*
\v 5 \wj They would never followВҰ71798 a strangerВҰ71794 becauseВҰ71804 they wouldn't know his voiceВҰ71810, in fact they'd run away from himВҰ71803.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \nd YeshuaВҰ71819\nd* told them this illustration, but none of thoseВҰ71820 who heard it knewВҰ71824 what it meant.
\s1 Yeshua is the good shepherd
\rem /s1 Jesus the Good Shepherd
\p
\v 7 SoВҰ71833 \nd Yeshua\nd* continuedВҰ71832, вҖң\wj Honestly I will tell youВҰ71842 that \+em I am\+em* the entrance for the sheepВҰ71852.\wj*
\v 8 \wj The ones who cameВҰ71855 beforeВҰ71856 me are thievesВҰ71859 andВҰ71861 robbersВҰ71862, butВҰ71863 the sheepВҰ71870 didn'tВҰ71864 listen to them.\wj*
\v 9 \wj \+em I am\+em* the entrance. Anyone who comes in via me will be savedВҰ71882, and will be able to go in and out and find pastureВҰ71888.\wj*
\v 10 \wj The thiefВҰ71892 only comes to stealВҰ71900 and killВҰ71904 and destroyВҰ71904, butВҰ71901 I cameВҰ71907 so that they could live, and live a full lifeВҰ71909.\wj*
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the good shepherdвҖ”the good shepherd gives hisВҰ71929 own lifeВҰ71928 for the sheepВҰ71934.\wj*\f + \fr 10:11 \ft See http://bibleandtech.blogspot.com/2021/04/john-1011-18-translations-and-notes-rcl.html\f*
\v 12 \wj The paid worker is not even the shepherdВҰ71942, because the sheep aren'tВҰ71940 his own and if he sees a wolf comingВҰ71956 he just abandons the sheep and takes off and the wolf scattersВҰ71969 the sheep and snatchesВҰ71966 someвҖ”\wj*
\v 13 \wj that's becauseВҰ71976 he's just a worker and doesn't really care aboutВҰ71985 the sheepВҰ71987.\wj*
\v 14 \wj \+em I am\+em* the goodВҰ71993 shepherdВҰ71991 and I know my \+add sheep\+add* and they know me,\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 10:15: \xt Mat 11:27; Luk 10:22.\x*\wj just like the father knows me and I know the fatherвҖ”in fact I will give myВҰ72023 life for the sheepВҰ72029.\wj*
\v 16 \wj I also have other sheep whichВҰ72035 are not in this fieldВҰ72041 andВҰ72030 it's appropriateВҰ72045 for me to bringВҰ72048 thoseВҰ72043 other sheep also, thenВҰ72030 they'll be hearingВҰ72053 myВҰ72052 voiceВҰ72051 because there'll be just one flockВҰ72059 with one shepherdВҰ72061.\wj*
\p
\v 17 \wj The fatherВҰ72066 loves me becauseВҰ72069 I am layingВҰ72071 down myВҰ72074 lifeВҰ72073 so that I can takeВҰ72077 itВҰ72078 back again.\wj*
\v 18 \wj No one is taking it from me, butВҰ72097 I'm layingВҰ72088 it down myselfВҰ72091. I have authority to lay it down, and also authority to take it back againВҰ72101 because I receivedВҰ72108 this commandВҰ72107 from myВҰ72114 fatherВҰ72113.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 19 The Jewish religious leaders were againВҰ72117 divided about Yeshua's teaching
\v 20 with many of them sayingВҰ72126, вҖңHe's got a demonВҰ72133,вҖқ and, вҖңHe's stark ravingВҰ72136 madвҖ”why are youВҰ72140 all even listening to himВҰ72139!вҖқ
\p
\v 21 But others were sayingВҰ72144, вҖңHe doesn't sound like he's demon-possessed. And how could a demon make a blindВҰ72158 man see?вҖқ
\s1 The Jewish leaders won't accept Yeshua's teaching
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Rejected
\rem /s1 The Unbelief of the Jews
\rem /s1 Jesus Claims to Be the Son of God
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Rejected by the Jews
\p
\v 22 By then it was winterВҰ72173 and the time for the Jewish Festival of Dedication in Yerushalem.
\v 23 \nd Yeshua\nd* was walkingВҰ72177 in the templeВҰ72183 in an area known as Solomon'sВҰ72188 Porch
\v 24 when he was surroundedВҰ72189 by the Jewish religious leaders and interrogated, вҖңHow long do you plan to keep us in suspenseВҰ72203 for? If you are the \nd messiahВҰ72208\nd*, just tell us clearly.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj I already told you all,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ72213, вҖң\wj butВҰ72220 you didn'tВҰ72221 believeВҰ72222 me. The miracles that I do with the authority of myВҰ72236 fatherВҰ72235 testifyВҰ72241 about me,\wj*
\v 26 \wj but you don'tВҰ72247 accept what the miracles point to becauseВҰ72249 you aren'tВҰ72247 part of my flock.\wj*
\v 27 \wj MyВҰ72268 sheepВҰ72263 listen to myВҰ72268 voiceВҰ72267, and I know them and theyВҰ72276 followВҰ72276 afterВҰ72277 me.\wj*
\v 28 \wj I give them lifeВҰ72283 which will never end so theyВҰ72288 won'tВҰ72287 ever be destroyed, and no one will be able to snatchВҰ72296 them away from me.\wj*
\v 29 \wj MyВҰ72306 father is the one who gaveВҰ72310 them to me, and he's more powerful than any other, so no one can snatchВҰ72323 them away from him.\wj*
\v 30 \wj The fatherВҰ72333 andВҰ72331 I are one.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 31 Again the Jewish leaders picked up rocksВҰ72340 to throw at him to kill him
\v 32 but \nd Yeshua\nd* asked them, вҖң\wj I showedВҰ72355 you all many miracles from myВҰ72362 fatherВҰ72361. Which miracle do you want to kill me for?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 10:33: \xt Lev 24:16.\x*They answeredВҰ72372, вҖңIt's not for any \em goodВҰ72379\em* deed that we think you deserve to die, butВҰ72387 becauseВҰ72388 you, a humanВҰ72390, dishonour \nd GodВҰ72395\nd* by claiming to be himВҰ72374.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 10:34: \xt Psa 82:6.\x*\nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ72396, вҖң\wj Isn't itВҰ72404 writtenВҰ72405 in yourВҰ72413 scriptures that God saidВҰ72416, вҖҳYou all are godsВҰ72417вҖҷ?\wj*
\v 35 \wj Now the scripturesВҰ72436 can'tВҰ72432 be wrong, andВҰ72431 if the ones who heard teaching from \+nd GodВҰ72429\+nd* were calledВҰ72421 godsВҰ72422,\wj*
\v 36 \wj why are youВҰ72446 telling the one that the fatherВҰ72439 blessed andВҰ72441 sentВҰ72442 out into the worldВҰ72445 that I am insultingВҰ72449 God becauseВҰ72450 I saidВҰ72451 that I'm God's son?\wj*
\v 37 \wj If I'm not doingВҰ72460 myВҰ72465 father'sВҰ72464 work, then you don'tВҰ72459 need to believeВҰ72467 that he sent me,\wj*
\v 38 \wj butВҰ72487 if I am doingВҰ72471 his work, even if you don'tВҰ72474 believe that he sent me, at least believe in what I do so that you all can know that the father is in me and I'm in the father.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 39 That was enough that they tried yet againВҰ72509 to arrestВҰ72510 him, but he was able to get out and away from theirВҰ72516 influence.
\p
\v 40 \x + \xo 10:40: \xt Yhn 1:28.\x*ThenВҰ72517 Yeshua crossed the YordanВҰ72523 river to the placeВҰ72526 whereВҰ72528 Yohan had immersedВҰ72534 the people, andВҰ72517 he stayed thereВҰ72538.
\v 41 Many people visited him there, andВҰ72539 they were sayingВҰ72545 that even though Yohan had never done even one miracle, on the otherВҰ72556 hand everything that he had said about Yeshua was true,
\v 42 andВҰ72565 many people thereВҰ72573 believedВҰ72569 that Yeshua was from God.
\c 11
\s1 Yeshua is aware of Lazarus' death from afar
\rem /s1 The Death of Lazarus
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 11:1: \xt Luk 10:38-39.\x*Now there was a manВҰ72576 called LazarusВҰ72579 who lived in the villageВҰ72584 of BethanyВҰ72581 along with his sistersВҰ72592 MarthaВҰ72589 andВҰ72587 MariaВҰ72586.
\v 2 \x + \xo 11:2: \xt Yhn 12:3.\x*(MariaВҰ72599 was the one who \jmp later|link-href="#C12V3"\jmp* poured fragrant oil over YeshuaВҰ72618 andВҰ72596 wipedВҰ72606 hisВҰ72609 feetВҰ72608 with herВҰ72612 hairВҰ72611.) ButВҰ72596 now their brotherВҰ72616 was seriously ill
\v 3 and so the two sistersВҰ72627 sentВҰ72621 a message to Yeshua sayingВҰ72634, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ72636\nd*, this man that youВҰ72639 love is seriously ill.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 However, when \nd Yeshua\nd* got the message he saidВҰ72651 \add to those around him\add*, вҖң\wj This sicknessВҰ72654 won'tВҰ72656 end in deathВҰ72659 butВҰ72648 in honour for \+nd GodВҰ72665\+nd*, so that his son will also be honoured because of it.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 5 Now it was true that \nd Yeshua\nd* loved the three of them.
\v 6 Yet when he heardВҰ72696 thatВҰ72706 Lazarus was sick, he stayed in the placeВҰ72709 where he was for twoВҰ72710 more daysВҰ72711
\v 7 before he said to his followers, вҖң\wj It's time to head down to YudeaВҰ72724 again.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 8 ButВҰ72739 they double-checked, вҖңHonoured teacher, the Yudeans wanted to execute you, so do you really want to go back thereВҰ72742 againВҰ72740?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 And \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ72743, вҖң\wj There are twelve hoursВҰ72749 of light in the day. Anyone who walks during the daytime doesn't stumbleВҰ72765 becauseВҰ72766 he is seeingВҰ72773 the light \+add that shines in\+add* this worldВҰ72770.\wj*
\v 10 \wj But anyoneВҰ72776 who walks at nightВҰ72780 will stumbleВҰ72781, becauseВҰ72782 the lightВҰ72784 is not in them.\wj*вҖқ
\v 11 And he continuedВҰ72791, вҖң\wj OurВҰ72801 friendВҰ72800 LazarusВҰ72797 has fallenВҰ72802 asleepВҰ72802, butВҰ72792 I'm goingВҰ72805 so that I can wake him up.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 But his followers objected, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ72818\nd*, \add it's good\add* if he's sleeping because it helps with healing.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 But \nd Yeshua\nd* had spokenВҰ72824 about Lazarus' deathВҰ72831вҖ”not just normal sleep as they had thought.
\v 14 SoВҰ72845 \nd YeshuaВҰ72850\nd* told them plainlyВҰ72851, вҖң\wj LazarusВҰ72852 is dead\wj*
\v 15 \wj and I'm glad that I wasn't thereВҰ72866, becauseВҰ72859 you all will benefit as yourВҰ72859 faith grows. Anyway, let's get moving.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ThomasВҰ72873 (nicknamed вҖҳTwinвҖҷ) grumbled to the others, вҖңYeah, we might as well go so thatВҰ72874 we can get killed as well.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is the resurrection and the life
\rem /s1 Jesus the Resurrection and the Life
\rem /s1 Jesus Comforts the Sisters
\p
\v 17 SoВҰ72889 when they eventually arrived, \nd LazarusВҰ72891\nd* body had alreadyВҰ72900 been in the burial chamber for fourВҰ72899 daysВҰ72901.
\v 18 The village of BethanyВҰ72911 was less than three kilometres from Yerushalem,
\v 19 so many of the Yudeans from there had comeВҰ72927 out to consoleВҰ72937 MarthaВҰ72932 andВҰ72933 MariaВҰ72935 after the death of theirВҰ72940 brotherВҰ72941.
\p
\v 20 As soon as MarthaВҰ72945 heardВҰ72947 that \nd Yeshua\nd* had arrived, she went out to meet him, butВҰ72955 MariaВҰ72954 stayed behind where she was sittingВҰ72961 in the houseВҰ72958.
\v 21 MarthaВҰ72966 cried, вҖң\nd Yeshua\nd*, \nd masterВҰ72971\nd*. If you'd been here, myВҰ72981 brotherВҰ72980 wouldn'tВҰ72977 have diedВҰ72978,
\v 22 because I already know that anything that you ask from \nd GodВҰ72998\nd*, he will give it to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj YourВҰ73011 brotherВҰ73010 will come back to life.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңYes, I know that he'll come back to life at the resurrectionВҰ73022 on the last dayВҰ73026,вҖқ said MarthaВҰ73015.
\p
\v 25 ButВҰ73037 \nd Yeshua\nd* continuedВҰ73027, вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the resurrectionВҰ73036 andВҰ73037 the lifeВҰ73039. Anyone who believesВҰ73041 that I'm from God, even if they dieВҰ73045 they'll still be livingВҰ73046,\wj*
\v 26 \wj and everyoneВҰ73049 who's alive and believes thatВҰ73050 I was sent from God, will not dieВҰ73058 in the \+add next\+add* age.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 Martha replied, вҖңYes, \nd masterВҰ73069\nd*, I do believeВҰ73072 that you'reВҰ73075 the \nd messiahВҰ73078\nd*, God's son, the one sent into this worldВҰ73086.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua weeps with his close friends
\rem /s1 Jesus Weeps
\p
\v 28 After saying this, Martha wentВҰ73093 and quietly calledВҰ73095 herВҰ73099 sisterВҰ73098 MariaВҰ73096, вҖңThe teacherВҰ73106 is on his way and he wants to see you.вҖқ
\v 29 SoВҰ73113 Maria quicklyВҰ73118 got up andВҰ73119 went to find himВҰ73123.
\v 30 At that stage, \nd Yeshua\nd* hadn't yet comeВҰ73128 into the villageВҰ73134 proper, butВҰ73135 was stillВҰ73137 at the edge whereВҰ73142 MarthaВҰ73146 had met himВҰ73144.
\v 31 The Yudean people who'd been sitting with MariaВҰ73162 in sympathy there in the houseВҰ73156, when they saw her get up quicklyВҰ73165 and go out, they assumed thatВҰ73150 she was goingВҰ73178 to the cemetery to weep there.
\p
\v 32 But when MariaВҰ73188 found \nd Yeshua\nd*, sheВҰ73190 knelt at hisВҰ73201 feetВҰ73205 and said, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ73209\nd*, if you'd been here myВҰ73217 brotherВҰ73220 wouldn't have diedВҰ73218.вҖқ
\p
\v 33 Now when \nd Yeshua\nd* sawВҰ73225 her weeping there, along with the others that had followed also weeping, he himselfВҰ73250 was quite affected and groanedВҰ73242 inside,
\v 34 butВҰ73251 he just asked, вҖң\wj WhereВҰ73253 has he been laid?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖң\nd MasterВҰ73259\nd*, come andВҰ73251 seeВҰ73262,вҖқ they replied.
\p
\v 35 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* \add broke down and\add* burst into tears,
\v 36 which made the others comment, вҖңSeeВҰ73271 how much he cared about him.вҖқ
\p
\v 37 But some of them mocked, вҖңThis is the man who could make a blindВҰ73291 man see again, yet how come he wasn't able to stop this man from dying!вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua calls Lazarus back to life
\rem /s1 Jesus Raises Lazarus to Life
\rem /s1 Jesus Raises Lazarus From the Dead
\rem /s1 Jesus Raises Lazarus from the Dead
\rem /s1 Lazarus Is Brought to Life
\p
\v 38 SoВҰ73312 \nd Yeshua\nd* who was still holding back sobs, went to the cemetery. Lazarus' body had been placed in a cave with a stoneВҰ73315 blocking it,
\v 39 and \nd Yeshua\nd* instructed them to take away the stoneВҰ73324.
\p MarthaВҰ73334 (the sisterВҰ73330 of the dead man) spoke up, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ73335\nd*, the stinkВҰ73337 will be bad becauseВҰ73339 it's alreadyВҰ73336 been four days.вҖқ
\p
\v 40 But \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ73346, вҖң\wj Didn't I tell you that if you would believeВҰ73350, then you would see God's power?\wj*вҖқ
\v 41 SoВҰ73369 they tookВҰ73357 the stoneВҰ73361 away and \nd Yeshua\nd* looked upwardsВҰ73375 and saidВҰ73377, вҖңFather, I thankВҰ73379 you that you listen to me.
\v 42 Actually I know that you alwaysВҰ73388 hearВҰ73390 me, butВҰ73385 I saidВҰ73397 that for the sake of these people so that they will believeВҰ73399 that itВҰ73397 was you who sentВҰ73403 me here.вҖқ
\v 43 After saying that, heВҰ73409 shouted, вҖң\wj LazarusВҰ73412, comeВҰ73413 out!\wj*вҖқ
\v 44 Then the man who had diedВҰ73419 \add slowly\add* shuffled outвҖ”still with linenВҰ73430 stripsВҰ73430 wrapped around his handsВҰ73428 and his feetВҰ73423, and a cloth wrapped around his faceВҰ73433.
\s1 The leaders create a plan to execute Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Plot against Jesus
\rem /s1 The Plot to Kill Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:1-5; Mark 14:1-2; Luke 22:1-2)
\p
\v 45 Because of that, many of the Yudeans believedВҰ73472 that Yeshua was from God after having followed MariaВҰ73462 andВҰ73463 seeing what Yeshua did.
\v 46 ButВҰ73483 others wentВҰ73479 andВҰ73483 told the Pharisee partyВҰ73482 what \nd Yeshua\nd* had done.
\v 47 SoВҰ73494 the chiefВҰ73496 priestsВҰ73496 and the Pharisee partyВҰ73499 called a formal meeting and asked, вҖңWhat should weВҰ73504 do becauseВҰ73506 this manВҰ73509 is doing many miracles.
\v 48 If we allowВҰ73517 him to continue like this, all the crowds will be believingВҰ73521 he's the messiah, and then the Romans will come and destroy both our temple and our governance.вҖқ
\p
\v 49 But one of them, CaiaphasВҰ73548 who was chiefВҰ73549 priestВҰ73549 that yearВҰ73552, spoke up, вҖңYou don'tВҰ73557 know anything.
\v 50 Don't you all realise that its better for all of us if one manВҰ73569 dies so that the peopleВҰ73573 and the nationВҰ73578 won'tВҰ73575 be destroyed?вҖқ
\v 51 (He didn'tВҰ73584 say this from his own thinking, butВҰ73581 beingВҰ73589 chiefВҰ73588 priestВҰ73588 that yearВҰ73591, he was announcing God's message that \nd Yeshua\nd* was goingВҰ73596 to die for the nationВҰ73603,
\v 52 andВҰ73604 not only for this nationВҰ73608, butВҰ73610 for all of God's childrenВҰ73614 scatteredВҰ73619 around the world to become united.)
\p
\v 53 As a result, from that dayВҰ73629 on they decided that Yeshua needed to be executed.
\v 54 Because of that, \nd Yeshua\nd* no longerВҰ73640 walked around Yudea in publicВҰ73641, butВҰ73646 wentВҰ73647 out to the townВҰ73659 of EphraimВҰ73657 out in the wildernessВҰ73655 andВҰ73660 stayed thereВҰ73637 with his followers.
\rem /s1 The Passover in Jerusalem
\p
\v 55 At that time, the Jewish Passover celebrations were approaching, andВҰ73678 many people from the regionsВҰ73687 wentВҰ73679 to Yerushalem ahead of the celebrations to purifyВҰ73695 themselvesВҰ73696.
\v 56 They were lookingВҰ73697 out for \nd Yeshua\nd* and as they stoodВҰ73709 around in the templeВҰ73708, they asked each other, вҖңWhat do you think? Surely he won'tВҰ73716 comeВҰ73717 to the celebrations.вҖқ
\v 57 The chiefВҰ73725 priestsВҰ73725 andВҰ73722 the Pharisee partyВҰ73728 had already announced that if anyoneВҰ73735 knew whereВҰ73737 Yeshua was, they must inform them so that they could arrestВҰ73742 himВҰ73743.
\c 12
\s1 Maria sacrifices expensive fragrant oil
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany
\rem /s1 Mary Anoints Jesus
\rem /s1 Jesus Anointed at Bethany
\r (Mat. 26:6-13; Mark 14:3-9)
\p
\v 1 Because of this, \nd Yeshua\nd* wentВҰ73753 to BethanyВҰ73755 six daysВҰ73750 beforeВҰ73747 the Passover. This was whereВҰ73756 LazarusВҰ73758 lived, the one he had brought back to life.
\v 2 SoВҰ73771 they prepared dinner for him thereВҰ73774 and MarthaВҰ73777 was servingВҰ73778 and LazarusВҰ73783 was among those sittingВҰ73788 with Yeshua.
\v 3 \x + \xo 12:3: \xt Luk 7:37-38.\x*Then MariaВҰ73794 took about 300g of very expensive nard oil and smeared it on \nd Yeshua's\nd* feet, and then wipedВҰ73810 off hisВҰ73816 feet with herВҰ73813 own hairВҰ73812, and the houseВҰ73820 was filledВҰ73821 with the fragrance of the oil.
\v 4 But YudasВҰ73832, one of Yeshua's apprenticesВҰ73838 (the one who would eventually turn him in) complained,
\v 5 вҖңHow come this lotion wasn't sold for almost a year's wages andВҰ73862 then the money givenВҰ73863 to the poor?вҖқ
\v 6 ButВҰ73882 he didn'tВҰ73871 say this because he cared for poor people, butВҰ73868 because he carried the purse for the group and used to steal from it.
\p
\v 7 But \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ73892, вҖң\wj Let herВҰ73897 continue. She has kept this for the time of myВҰ73904 burialВҰ73903.\wj*
\v 8 \x + \xo 12:8: \xt Deu 15:11.\x*\wj You'll always have poor people with you, but you won'tВҰ73917 always have me here.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The leaders also plan to kill Lazarus
\rem /s1 The Plot against Lazarus
\rem /s1 The Plot to Kill Lazarus
\p
\v 9 When it was discovered that Yeshua was thereВҰ73932 \add in Bethany\add*, many Yudeans started arriving, not only becauseВҰ73937 of Yeshua, butВҰ73941 also to seeВҰ73947 LazarusВҰ73945 who'd been deadВҰ73953 andВҰ73934 Yeshua had brought him back to life.
\v 10 But the chiefВҰ73960 priestsВҰ73960 decided in a meeting that theyВҰ73965 should also have LazarusВҰ73964 killed,
\v 11 because many people were ignoring them andВҰ73975 instead were believingВҰ73976 that \nd Yeshua\nd* \add came from God\add*.
\s1 Yeshua rides into Yerushalem with many cheers
\rem /s1 The Triumphant Entry into Jerusalem
\rem /s1 The Triumphal Entry
\rem /s1 Jesus' Triumphal Entry into Jerusalem
\r (Mat. 21:1-11; Mark 11:1-11; Luke 19:28-40)
\p
\v 12 The next dayВҰ73981 a large crowdВҰ73984 of people who had comeВҰ73988 for the celebrations and had heardВҰ73993 that \nd Yeshua\nd* was comingВҰ73995 to Yerushalem
\v 13 \x + \xo 12:13: \xt Psa 118:25-26.\x*tookВҰ74001 \add long\add* branchesВҰ74003 from palm treesВҰ74005 and brought them out as they wentВҰ74007 to meet himВҰ74012. They called out, вҖңHonouredВҰ74019 saviourВҰ74019! The one comingВҰ74023 in \nd Yahweh's\nd* authority has been blessedВҰ74021 \add by God\add*. This is Yisrael's kingВҰ74029.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 Now \nd Yeshua\nd* had foundВҰ74032 a young donkeyВҰ74036 andВҰ74033 rode it \add into the city\add* just like it was writtenВҰ74042 in the scriptures,
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 12:15: \xt Zech 9:9.\x*вҖңDon't be worried youВҰ74051 children of Tsiyyon/ZionВҰ74047. YourВҰ74051 kingВҰ74050 is comingВҰ74052 mounted on a donkey'sВҰ74057 foal.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 (\nd Yeshua's\nd* apprentices didn'tВҰ74060 realise all these things at the time, butВҰ74087 it was later after Yeshua was lifted up to heaven that they were remindedВҰ74075 that these things had been writtenВҰ74086 about him, and that they had \add indeed\add* happened to him.)
\p
\v 17 People in the crowdВҰ74094 were telling each other about how they'd been with Yeshua when he'd calledВҰ74103 LazarusВҰ74102 out from the burial chamber and brought him back to life,
\v 18 So because of this, others also wanted to met Yeshua because they'd heardВҰ74124 that he'd done that miracle.
\v 19 SoВҰ74133 the Pharisees discussed this together, вҖңWe're getting nowhere with this. Look, it seems like the whole worldВҰ74147 wants to follow himВҰ74150.вҖқ
\s1 Some Greeks want to meet Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts His Death
\rem /s1 Some Greeks Seek Jesus
\rem /s1 Some Greeks Wish to See Jesus
\p
\v 20 And some Greek people were also goingВҰ74160 to Yerushalem to worship God at the celebrations
\v 21 and theyВҰ74179 approachedВҰ74170 PhilipВҰ74172 from BethsaidaВҰ74175 (up in GalileeВҰ74177) and asked himВҰ74180, вҖңMisterВҰ74182, we'd like to meet this \nd YeshuaВҰ74185\nd*.вҖқ
\v 22 So PhilipВҰ74189 went and told AndrewВҰ74193, and the two of them went and told \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\s1 Yeshua predicts his death again
\p
\v 23 Now \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj The time has comeВҰ74214 for humanity's child to be honoured.\wj*
\v 24 \wj I can assure you that unless a wheatВҰ74232 seed drops into the groundВҰ74236 and dies, it will stay just as it is, but if it dies, it's able to produceВҰ74245 a harvest.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 12:25: \xt Mat 10:39; 16:25; Mrk 8:35; Luk 9:24; 17:33.\x*\wj Anyone who loves their life will lose it, butВҰ74255 the person hatingВҰ74257 their life in this worldВҰ74263 will stay alive forever.\wj*
\v 26 \wj Anyone who wants to serve me needsВҰ74282 to followВҰ74282 afterВҰ74281 me, so that whereverВҰ74284 I am, my servantВҰ74292 will also be thereВҰ74289. Anyone who serves me will be honouredВҰ74303 by the fatherВҰ74306.\wj*
\rem /s1 Jesus Speaks about His Death
\p
\v 27 \wj Now, I'm very troubled. What else could I sayВҰ74315 other than, вҖҳFather, let me avoid what's comingвҖҷ? ButВҰ74313 it was exactly this that I cameВҰ74326 for.\wj*
\v 28 \wj Father, may yourВҰ74335 authority be honoured.\wj*вҖқ
\p And a voiceВҰ74354 from the sky answered, вҖңI've already brought honourВҰ74333 to it and will do so againВҰ74362.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 This caused some in the crowdВҰ74367 standing there to say that they'd heardВҰ74371 thunderВҰ74375 while others said that a messengerВҰ74384 must have spokenВҰ74386 to Yeshua.
\p
\v 30 вҖң\wj That voiceВҰ74399 wasn't for myВҰ74395 sake,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ74392, вҖң\wj butВҰ74403 for all of youВҰ74405.\wj*
\v 31 \wj This world is about to be judgedВҰ74407 and its rulerВҰ74414 will be thrownВҰ74419 out,\wj*
\v 32 \wj andВҰ74422 when I'm lifted up\wj*\f + \fr 12:32 \ft lifted up / exalted: See https://bibleDifferences.net/2019/04/25/156-exulted\f* \wj from the earthВҰ74431, I will attract everyone towards me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 33 By sayingВҰ74441 this, he was indicating how he was goingВҰ74445 to die.
\p
\v 34 \x + \xo 12:34: \xt Psa 110:4; Isa 9:7; Eze 37:25; Dan 7:14.\x*SoВҰ74448 the crowdВҰ74451 queried himВҰ74449, вҖңWe heardВҰ74453 from the scriptures that the \nd messiahВҰ74459\nd* will stay until the end of the age so why do youВҰ74468 say that humanity's child will be lifted up? And who is this вҖҳhumanity's childвҖҷ?вҖқ
\p
\v 35 \nd Yeshua\nd* answered them, вҖң\wj The light will be among you all for just a littleВҰ74490 bit longer, so get walking whileВҰ74501 you have the light so that you won'tВҰ74507 have to deal with darkness. Anyone walking in the dark doesn't know whereВҰ74522 they're goingВҰ74523.\wj*
\v 36 \wj WhileВҰ74524 you still have the light, believeВҰ74529 in the light so that you will becomeВҰ74537 children of light.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Jews Continue in Their Unbelief
\rem /s1 The Unbelief of the People
\p \nd YeshuaВҰ74541\nd* said theseВҰ74538 things and then after leaving them, he was hiddenВҰ74546 from them.
\s1 Many people refuse to stand for Yeshua
\p
\v 37 Even though Yeshua had done so many miracles in front of the people, theyВҰ74558 didn'tВҰ74557 believeВҰ74558 that he was the messiah.
\v 38 \x + \xo 12:38: \xt Isa 53:1 (LXX).\x*This fulfilledВҰ74568 what the prophetВҰ74567 Yeshayah wrote,
\q1 вҖң\nd YahwehВҰ74571\nd*, who believedВҰ74573 ourВҰ74576 reportВҰ74575?
\q1 And who was \nd Yahweh's\nd* power revealedВҰ74582 to?вҖқ
\p
\v 39 BecauseВҰ74583 of this, theyВҰ74586 weren't able to believeВҰ74587, and again as YeshayahВҰ74593 wrote,
\q1
\v 40 \x + \xo 12:40: \xt Isa 6:10 (LXX).\x*вҖңHe has blindedВҰ74594 their eyes and maimedВҰ74600 their emotions,
\q1 so that they can'tВҰ74606 see with their eyes and understandВҰ74612 with their minds,
\q2 or they might be turnedВҰ74618 and then I would heal them.вҖқ
\p
\v 41 Yeshayah wrote this becauseВҰ74629 he sawВҰ74632 the messiah's greatness and spokeВҰ74639 concerningВҰ74640 him.
\v 42 LikewiseВҰ74642, many of the Jewish leaders believedВҰ74650 that Yeshua was the messiah, but they didn't tell others becauseВҰ74654 they didn't want the Pharisee partyВҰ74656 to banish them from their services
\v 43 as theyВҰ74664 valued the praise of people more than praise from \nd GodВҰ74676\nd*.
\s1 It's Yeshua's teachings that will judge the hearers
\rem /s1 Judgment by Jesus' Words
\rem /s1 Summary of Jesus' Teaching
\p
\v 44 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* called out, вҖң\wj Anyone who believes that I came from God is not \+add just\+add* believing in me, butВҰ74680 \+add also\+add* believing in the one who sent me,\wj*
\v 45 \wj andВҰ74701 anyone who watches me \+add working\+add*, is watching the one who sentВҰ74708 me.\wj*
\v 46 \wj I came into this worldВҰ74714 as lightВҰ74711 so thatВҰ74718 anyone who believesВҰ74719 in me won'tВҰ74725 have darknessВҰ74724 residing in them.\wj*
\v 47 \wj I won'tВҰ74738 be judgingВҰ74744 anyoneВҰ74730 who hears myВҰ74731 teaching andВҰ74737 doesn't obey it, becauseВҰ74747 I didn'tВҰ74738 come to judgeВҰ74750 the world butВҰ74753 rather to saveВҰ74755 it.\wj*
\v 48 \wj Anyone who rejectsВҰ74759 me andВҰ74761 doesn't accept myВҰ74766 teaching does have a judge thoughвҖ”it's the messageВҰ74772 that I spokeВҰ74774 that will judge them at the end of time\wj*
\v 49 \wj because I wasn't speakingВҰ74805 from my own thoughts, butВҰ74803 it was the fatherВҰ74794 himselfВҰ74795 who sentВҰ74792 me that told me what to sayВҰ74802 and what to teach.\wj*
\v 50 \wj And I'm fully aware that \+add obeying\+add* hisВҰ74811 commandsВҰ74810 leads to living forever. ThereforeВҰ74818 whenever I speak, I just say whatever the fatherВҰ74826 saidВҰ74823 to me.\wj*вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 Yeshua washes the feet of his apprentices
\rem /s1 Jesus Washes the Disciples' Feet
\rem /s1 Jesus Washes His Disciples' Feet
\rem /s1 Farewell discourses
\p
\v 1 Even beforeВҰ74829 the actual feast part of the Passover celebrations, \nd Yeshua\nd* knew that his time had comeвҖ”the time when he would leave this world andВҰ74830 \add return\add* to the fatherВҰ74855. He loved his followers who were in the world right through to the endВҰ74865.
\p
\v 2 And now it was getting near time for the dinner andВҰ74868 the devilВҰ74874 had alreadyВҰ74875 put into YudasВҰ74883 Iscariot's mindВҰ74879 \add the idea\add* of handing Yeshua over \add to the authorities\add*.
\v 3 Yeshua knew that the fatherВҰ74903 had givenВҰ74899 everything to him, putting it under his control, and he knew that he had come from God and would return to God.
\v 4 So he got up from the dinner \add table\add*, changed out of his clothesВҰ74927, and wrapped a linenВҰ74931 towelВҰ74931 around himselfВҰ74934.
\v 5 Then he put waterВҰ74938 into the wash bowl and started washingВҰ74947 the feetВҰ74949 of his apprenticesВҰ74951, wipingВҰ74954 them dry with the linenВҰ74956 towelВҰ74956 thatВҰ74957 he was wearing wrapped around him.
\v 6 After he'd washed a few, he got to SimonВҰ74964 PeterВҰ74965 who asked him, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ74971\nd*, are you going to wash myВҰ74973 feetВҰ74976?вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj What I'm doingВҰ74985 now,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ74977, вҖң\wj you won'tВҰ74988 really understand, butВҰ74979 in the future you will.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Peter responded, вҖңWell I'm never ever going to let you wash \em my\em* feetВҰ75010!вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj If I don'tВҰ75004 wash them,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ75015, вҖң\wj then you won'tВҰ75004 be included in my \+add group\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңWell, if that's so,вҖқ PeterВҰ75032 said, вҖңdon'tВҰ75035 just wash my feetВҰ75038 butВҰ75041 my handsВҰ75044 andВҰ75045 my headВҰ75047 as well.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj Any person who's already washedВҰ75053 \+add themselves\+add* only needs to wash their feetВҰ75065 now to be clean. And so you're clean, butВҰ75074 not every one of you.\wj*вҖқ
\v 11 He saidВҰ75089 this last bit becauseВҰ75087 he already knew who was going to hand him over.
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 13:12-15: \xt Luk 22:27.\x*SoВҰ75096 when he'd finished washing theirВҰ75100 feetВҰ75099, he got dressed againВҰ75111 and satВҰ75110 down and asked, вҖң\wj Do you know what I just did to you all?\wj*
\v 13 \wj You call me teacher and \+nd masterВҰ75125\+nd*, and so youВҰ75128 should, becauseВҰ75131 I am.\wj*
\v 14 \wj SoВҰ75145 if the \+nd masterВҰ75153\+nd* and teacher of you all washedВҰ75147 yourВҰ75148 feet, then you also oughtВҰ75162 to wash each other's feet.\wj*
\v 15 \wj I have given this to you all as an exampleВҰ75168 that you can also do to others.\wj*
\v 16 \x + \xo 13:16: \xt Mat 10:24; Luk 6:40; Yhn 15:20.\x*\wj I can assure you that a slaveВҰ75188 isn't greater than hisВҰ75192 masterВҰ75191, and a missionary isn't greater than the \+add king\+add* who sends him.\wj*
\v 17 \wj If you can figure all this out and then do it, you will be blessedВҰ75204 \+add by God\+add*.\wj*
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts His Betrayal
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 13:18: \xt Psa 41:9.\x*вҖң\wj But I'm not talkingВҰ75213 aboutВҰ75210 all of youВҰ75212. I know each one that I choseВҰ75219, butВҰ75220 this that was \+add written\+add* in the scripturesВҰ75224 must be fulfilledВҰ75225,\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳThe one sharing foodВҰ75231 with me, liftedВҰ75232 up hisВҰ75238 boot againstВҰ75234 me.вҖҷ\wj*
\m
\v 19 \wj So I'm tellingВҰ75241 you now beforeВҰ75243 it happens so that when it does happen, then you'll all believeВҰ75247 that I am \+add the messiah\+add*.\wj*
\v 20 \x + \xo 13:20: \xt Mat 10:40; Mrk 9:37; Luk 9:48; 10:16.\x*\wj I can assure youВҰ75259 all that anyone who accepts any person that I might sendВҰ75266, they're accepting me, andВҰ75271 anyone who accepts me, is accepting the one who sentВҰ75278 me.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua indicates who will hand him over
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Betrayal
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts His Betrayal
\r (Mat. 26:20-25; Mark 14:17-21; Luke 22:21-23)
\p
\v 21 After sayingВҰ75294 theseВҰ75280 things, \nd Yeshua's\nd* thoughts were troubled and he said, вҖң\wj I can assure you that one of you will be turning me in.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 This made his apprenticesВҰ75312 glance around at each other, puzzled about which one he was talkingВҰ75318 about.
\v 23 \nd One\nd* of them that \nd Yeshua\nd* especially liked,\f + \fr 13:23 \ft This apprentice, unnamed here, is assumed to be the author of this account (being shy or modest).\f* was leaning against himВҰ75326 \add at the table\add*.
\v 24 SoВҰ75339 SimonВҰ75341 PeterВҰ75342 nodded to him to find out who Yeshua had been talkingВҰ75360 aboutВҰ75358,
\v 25 and he leanedВҰ75363 back on \nd Yeshua\nd* and asked \add quietly\add*, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ75375\nd*, who is it?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj It's the one I hand this piece of bread to after I've dipped it \+add in the sauce\+add*,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ75378. ThenВҰ75397 after dipping his piece of bread in, he gave it to YudasВҰ75408 IscariotВҰ75412.
\v 27 After \add Yudas accepted\add* the pieceВҰ75416 of breadВҰ75416, SatanВҰ75422 entered into him, andВҰ75413 thenВҰ75413 \nd Yeshua\nd* told him, вҖңWhat you'reВҰ75430 about to do, do it soon.вҖқ
\v 28 ButВҰ75435 none of the others sittingВҰ75439 around the table knewВҰ75437 what Yeshua meant.
\v 29 Some of them thought that since YudasВҰ75455 held their purse, perhaps \nd Yeshua\nd* was getting himВҰ75458 to buy something they needed for the feastВҰ75469 or to giveВҰ75475 something to the poor.
\p
\v 30 Anyway, havingВҰ75476 eaten the pieceВҰ75479 of breadВҰ75479, Yudas wentВҰ75482 straight outside where itВҰ75484 was already dark.
\s1 The new command to love each other
\rem /s1 The New Commandment
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial
\p
\v 31 After Yudas had gone, \nd Yeshua\nd* told the others, вҖң\wj Now humanity's child will be honoured andВҰ75499 \+nd GodВҰ75501\+nd* will be honoured through himВҰ75504.\wj*
\v 32 \wj Also \+nd GodВҰ75514\+nd* himselfВҰ75518 will be honouring him and will do that immediatelyВҰ75521.\wj*
\v 33 \wj My friends, I'll only be with you a littleВҰ75528 bit longer. Then you'll all look for me and as I told\wj*\x + \xo 13:33: \xt Yhn 7:34.\x* \wj the religious leaders, you won'tВҰ75547 be able to go where I'm goingВҰ75544. So now I've also told all of you.\wj*
\v 34 \x + \xo 13:34: \xt Yhn 15:12,17; 1Yhn 3:23; 2Yhn 5.\x*\wj I'm givingВҰ75557 you a new commandВҰ75555вҖ”you need to love each other. The way that I lovedВҰ75565 all of you is how you should love each other.\wj*
\v 35 \wj This is actually how you'll know if you're my followers: if you're loving each other.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua predicts that Peter will disown him
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells Peter's Denial
\r (Mat. 26:31-35; Mark 14:27-31; Luke 22:31-34)
\p
\v 36 Now PeterВҰ75596 followed-up, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ75597\nd*, whereВҰ75598 are you going?вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj WhereВҰ75605 I'm going,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ75600, вҖң\wj you won'tВҰ75608 be able to follow me at this stage, but you will follow me eventually.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 37 PeterВҰ75626 asked again, вҖңWhy can'tВҰ75630 I followВҰ75636 afterВҰ75633 you now? I'm prepared to give myВҰ75643 lifeВҰ75642 for you.вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖң\wj You think you'll be giving yourВҰ75657 lifeВҰ75656 for me?\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* responded. вҖң\wj I can assure you thatВҰ75673 the roosterВҰ75669 won'tВҰ75668 crow untilВҰ75672 you've already disownedВҰ75675 knowing me threeВҰ75679 times.\wj*вҖқ
\c 14
\s1 Yeshua is the road to the father but will be leaving
\rem /s1 Jesus, the Way to the Father
\rem /s1 Jesus the Way to the Father
\rem /s1 Jesus Comforts His Disciples
\p
\v 1 \add Yeshua continued telling them,\add* вҖң\wj Don't be living in fear. You believe that \+nd GodВҰ75693\+nd* is real, and you also believe that I was sent by him.\wj*
\v 2 \wj There are many places to live in myВҰ75703 father'sВҰ75702 residenceвҖ”I wouldВҰ75712 have told you if there wasn't becauseВҰ75714 I'm goingВҰ75715 there to prepareВҰ75716 a placeВҰ75717 for all of you.\wj*
\v 3 \wj And after I've gone to prepareВҰ75725 that placeВҰ75728, thenВҰ75721 I'llВҰ75736 be comingВҰ75733 back againВҰ75732 andВҰ75721 will bring you to myselfВҰ75739, so that whereВҰ75741 I am, you can all be there also.\wj*
\v 4 \wj You know how to get whereВҰ75750 I'm goingВҰ75752.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Jesus the Way to the Father
\p
\v 5 вҖң\nd MasterВҰ75764\nd*,вҖқ Thomas asked, вҖңwe don'tВҰ75765 \add even\add* know \em whereВҰ75767\em* you'reВҰ75768 goingВҰ75768, let alone how to get there.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 And \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the pathВҰ75785 and the truthВҰ75788 and the lifeВҰ75791. No one can get to the fatherВҰ75796 exceptВҰ75797 via me.\wj*
\v 7 \wj If you had all known me, you would also have known myВҰ75808 fatherВҰ75807, and from now on you do know him and have seen him.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 8 So Philip said, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ75826\nd*, show us the fatherВҰ75830 andВҰ75831 that'll be enough for us.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj I've been with you all for quite some timeВҰ75840,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj and yet you still don'tВҰ75846 \+add even\+add* know me, PhilipВҰ75849.\wj*
\v 10 \wj You don't believeВҰ75867 that I am in the father and the father is in me. These things that I've been telling you all, I don't \+add just\+add* make them up myselfВҰ75889, butВҰ75874 the father who lives in me is doingВҰ75900 what he wants.\wj*
\v 11 \wj You all need to believe that I am in the father and the father is in me. If that's hard, at least believe it becauseВҰ75925 of what he's doing.\wj*
\v 12 \wj I can assure youВҰ75936 all that anyone who believesВҰ75938 \+add that God sent\+add* me and is the source of the miracles that I do, that person will be able to do the same and even greaterВҰ75950 miracles becauseВҰ75953 I am goingВҰ75959 to the fatherВҰ75957.\wj*
\v 13 \wj Whatever youВҰ75966 requestВҰ75966 from me with myВҰ75973 nameВҰ75972 andВҰ75961 authority, I will do it so that the fatherВҰ75979 might be honoured because of the son.\wj*
\v 14 \wj Anything that youВҰ75986 all requestВҰ75986 using myВҰ75991 nameВҰ75990 and authority will be done.\wj*
\s1 The father will be sending a different advocate
\rem /s1 The Promise of the Holy Spirit
\rem /s1 Jesus Promises the Holy Spirit
\p
\v 15 вҖң\wj If you all love me, you will obey my commandsВҰ76000.\wj*
\v 16 \wj And I will ask the fatherВҰ76012 andВҰ76006 he will give you anotherВҰ76015 assistant to be with you all for this ageвҖ”\wj*
\v 17 \wj the \+nd spiritВҰ76033\+nd* of truthВҰ76035. The worldВҰ76038 cannot accept him, because it doesn't see or know him.\wj*
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj And I won'tВҰ76065 leave you all here as orphansВҰ76068, but I will come back to you.\wj*
\v 19 \wj It won't be long now and the worldВҰ76076 won't see me any more, butВҰ76074 you will see me becauseВҰ76084 I'll be alive and you all will be alive also.\wj*
\v 20 \wj At that time you will know that I am in myВҰ76104 fatherВҰ76103, and you all are in me, and I am in you all.\wj*
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj Anyone who takes my commandsВҰ76117 and obeys them, that's the person who loves me, and anyone who loves me will be lovedВҰ76131 by my fatherВҰ76135, and I \+add too\+add* will be loving them and will be revealing myselfВҰ76146 to them.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 Yudas (not Yudas IscariotВҰ76156) asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ76158\nd*, what's goingВҰ76165 on? Why would youВҰ76165 reveal yourselfВҰ76170 to us andВҰ76171 not to the \add whole\add* worldВҰ76174?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ76175, вҖң\wj If anyoneВҰ76182 loves me, they'll obey my teaching, and my fatherВҰ76192 will love them and we will go to that person and live with them.\wj*
\v 24 \wj ButВҰ76224 anyone who doesn't love me, won'tВҰ76213 obey my teaching. The words that youВҰ76230 hearВҰ76230 from me are not my own, butВҰ76234 come from the fatherВҰ76238 who sentВҰ76236 me.\wj*
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj I told you all this while I have been here with you all.\wj*
\v 26 \wj ButВҰ76267 the holy \+nd spiritВҰ76250\+nd*, the assistant who the fatherВҰ76257 will be sendingВҰ76254 with myВҰ76262 authority, he will be teachingВҰ76265 you everything, and will be remindingВҰ76268 you of everything thatВҰ76271 I told you all.\wj*
\p
\v 27 \wj I will leave peace with you all. I'm giving my peace to you all, but what I'm giving isn'tВҰ76285 like what the worldВҰ76288 gives. Don't be upset or afraid.\wj*
\v 28 \wj You all heardВҰ76301 me say that I'm going away and then will be comingВҰ76308 back. If you really loved me, you'd be very happy that I'm going to the father, becauseВҰ76324 the father is greaterВҰ76328 than me.\wj*
\p
\v 29 \wj ButВҰ76331 I'veВҰ76333 told you now beforeВҰ76335 it happens, so that when it does come to pass, you'll be able to believeВҰ76340 \+add that it was preplanned\+add*.\wj*
\v 30 \wj I won'tВҰ76357 have much more time to talk to you, becauseВҰ76348 the rulerВҰ76353 of the worldВҰ76351 is comingВҰ76347 and he has nothingВҰ76359 in common with me,\wj*
\v 31 \wj butВҰ76370 he's coming so that the worldВҰ76365 can know that I love the father and whatever the father told me to do, I'm doingВҰ76379 it.\wj*
\p вҖң\wj Come on, stand up. We need to be leaving this place.\wj*вҖқ
\c 15
\s1 The branches must stay connected to the vine
\rem /s1 Jesus, the True Vine
\rem /s1 Jesus the Real Vine
\rem /s1 The Vine and the Branches
\rem /s1 Jesus the True Vine
\p
\v 1 вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the true vineВҰ76386 andВҰ76389 myВҰ76392 fatherВҰ76391 is the farmerВҰ76394.\wj*
\v 2 \wj He removes everyВҰ76407 one of my branches that doesn't bear fruit, butВҰ76406 those that do bear fruit, he prunes them so they'll produceВҰ76403 even more.\wj*
\v 3 \wj You are all cleanВҰ76425 alreadyВҰ76423 becauseВҰ76427 of the teaching thatВҰ76430 I'veВҰ76431 given youВҰ76433.\wj*
\v 4 \wj Stay in me, and I will stay in you all, because just as a branchВҰ76443 can'tВҰ76444 bear fruitВҰ76446 in isolation when it's not connected to the vineВҰ76456, neitherВҰ76458 can you if you don'tВҰ76444 stay in me.\wj*
\p
\v 5 вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the vineВҰ76473 and you all are the branchesВҰ76476. Anyone who stays in me will produceВҰ76486 a lot of fruitВҰ76486вҖ”apartВҰ76489 from me you can'tВҰ76491 do anything.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Anyone who doesn't stay in me will be thrown away like a branchВҰ76510, and will witherВҰ76512 and be gatheredВҰ76514 togetherВҰ76514 with others, and thrown into the fireВҰ76520 to be burnt.\wj*
\v 7 \wj If you stay in me and myВҰ76534 teaching stays in you, then you can requestВҰ76544 whateverВҰ76538 you all want and itВҰ76547 will be done for you.\wj*
\v 8 \wj MyВҰ76554 fatherВҰ76553 will be honoured and praised when you produceВҰ76556 a lot of fruitВҰ76556, and you all becomeВҰ76562 myВҰ76554 followers.\wj*
\v 9 \wj I loved you all just as the fatherВҰ76572 loved me, so stay in my love.\wj*
\v 10 \wj If you obey my commands, you all will be staying in my love, just like I'veВҰ76598 obeyed my father'sВҰ76602 commands and I am staying in hisВҰ76611 love.\wj*
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj I'veВҰ76617 told you theseВҰ76615 things so that I'll be happy with you all, and so that yourВҰ76631 happiness will be genuine and long-lasting.\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 15:12: \xt Yhn 13:34; 15:17; 1Yhn 3:23; 2Yhn 5.\x*\wj So here's my request: keep lovingВҰ76640 each other just like I lovedВҰ76644 youВҰ76645 all.\wj*
\v 13 \wj No one has greaterВҰ76646 loveВҰ76648 than the one who gives up their own lifeВҰ76656 for their friendsВҰ76663.\wj*
\v 14 \wj You are myВҰ76669 friendsВҰ76668 if you do what I am telling you.\wj*
\v 15 \wj I'm not calling you slavesВҰ76684, because a slaveВҰ76687 doesn't know hisВҰ76692 master'sВҰ76694 plans, butВҰ76696 I'm calling you friendsВҰ76699 because I'veВҰ76697 told you everything that I heardВҰ76704 from myВҰ76709 fatherВҰ76708.\wj*
\v 16 \wj You didn'tВҰ76712 choose me, butВҰ76720 I chose you all, and I assigned you to go and produceВҰ76729 fruit and for yourВҰ76735 fruit to be permanent so that whateverВҰ76739 you requestВҰ76743 from the fatherВҰ76746 in myВҰ76750 name and authority, he will give it to you.\wj*
\v 17 \wj I am telling you all this so that you can all love each other.\wj*
\s1 People will hate Yeshua-followers
\rem /s1 The World's Hatred
\rem /s1 The World Hates the Disciples
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj If the worldВҰ76762 hates you, you all know that it hated me beforeВҰ76770 it hated you.\wj*
\v 19 \wj If you belonged to this world, then the world wouldВҰ76780 love you as it loves itsВҰ76781 own people, but you don'tВҰ76793 belong to this world because I choseВҰ76798 you out of it. That's why they hate all of you.\wj*
\v 20 \x + \xo 15:20: \xt Mat 10:24; Luk 6:40; Yhn 13:16.\x*\wj Remember that I told you that slavesВҰ76829 are not greaterВҰ76830 than their masterВҰ76832. So if they persecuted me, they'll also be persecuting you all. (If they'd obeyed myВҰ76843 teaching, they would also obey your teaching.)\wj*
\v 21 \wj But they will do all theseВҰ76851 things againstВҰ76855 youВҰ76857 because of myВҰ76861 nameВҰ76860, because they don'tВҰ76863 know the father who sentВҰ76866 me.\wj*
\v 22 \wj They wouldn't be considered sinners exceptВҰ76868 that I came and spokeВҰ76872 to them, so now they don'tВҰ76875 have any excuseВҰ76879 for theirВҰ76885 sin.\wj*
\v 23 \wj Anyone who hates me, also hates myВҰ76892 fatherВҰ76891.\wj*
\v 24 \wj If I hadn't done miracles amongВҰ76899 them of the sort that no one else has done, they wouldn't be considered to be sinners, butВҰ76914 now they've observed me and hatedВҰ76915 both me and myВҰ76921 fatherВҰ76920.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 15:25: \xt Psa 35:19; 69:4.\x*\wj The writings of the prophets will certainly come to pass, thatВҰ76927 вҖҳthey hatedВҰ76936 me undeservedlyВҰ76938вҖҷ.\wj*
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj When the assistant arrives that I will send to you all from the father, the \+nd spiritВҰ76955\+nd* of truth coming from the father, he will tell the truth about me.\wj*
\v 27 \wj You also will be able to tell the truth about me becauseВҰ76972 you all were with me from the beginningВҰ76974.\wj*
\c 16
\p
\v 1 вҖң\wj I'veВҰ76979 told you this so that you won'tВҰ76982 stumbleВҰ76983.\wj*
\v 2 \wj First they will ban you all from their religious services, then there's a time comingВҰ76990 when people will kill you thinking they're actually doing a sacredВҰ76998 serviceВҰ76998 to \+nd GodВҰ77002\+nd*,\wj*
\v 3 \wj butВҰ77003 they'll be doingВҰ77005 theseВҰ77004 things becauseВҰ77008 they don'tВҰ77009 know either the fatherВҰ77012 or me.\wj*
\v 4 \wj I've told you these things so that when they happen in the future, you'll rememberВҰ77026 that I've already told you aboutВҰ77028 them.\wj*
\s1 The work of God's spirit
\rem /s1 The Work of the Holy Spirit
\rem /s1 The Work of the Spirit
\p вҖң\wj I didn'tВҰ77039 tell you all of this right at the beginningВҰ77037 becauseВҰ77041 I was with you all,\wj*
\v 5 \wj butВҰ77046 soon I'll be returning to the one who sent me. Yet none of you are askingВҰ77057 me where I'll be going,\wj*
\v 6 \wj rather you are all just weighed down becauseВҰ77063 I'veВҰ77065 told you theseВҰ77064 things.\wj*
\v 7 \wj But honestly it's for your benefitВҰ77079 that I will leave here, becauseВҰ77085 if I don'tВҰ77087, then the assistant won'tВҰ77087 be comingВҰ77093 to you. But after I've gone, I'llВҰ77103 send himВҰ77104 to you all.\wj*
\v 8 \wj WhenВҰ77107 he comes, he'll scold the worldВҰ77112 about sinВҰ77114 and teach them about righteousnessВҰ77117 and judgementВҰ77120вҖ”\wj*
\v 9 \wj about sinВҰ77122 becauseВҰ77124 theyВҰ77126 don'tВҰ77125 believeВҰ77126 that I was sent by God,\wj*
\v 10 \wj about righteousnessВҰ77130 becauseВҰ77132 I am goingВҰ77137 to the fatherВҰ77135 and youВҰ77140 won't be able to see me any longerВҰ77139,\wj*
\v 11 \wj and about judgementВҰ77144 becauseВҰ77145 the rulerВҰ77147 of this worldВҰ77149 has been judgedВҰ77151.\wj*
\p
\v 12 вҖң\wj I stillВҰ77152 have a lot to tell you all, but you're not able to handle it all right now.\wj*
\v 13 \wj ButВҰ77198 when the assistant comes, the \+nd spiritВҰ77169\+nd* of truth, he will guide you in all truth becauseВҰ77186 he won'tВҰ77185 be speaking from his own thoughts, butВҰ77165 will tell you what he's been told, and he will explain to you what's still going to happen.\wj*
\v 14 \wj He'll be honouring me becauseВҰ77208 he'll take what is mine andВҰ77213 will explain it to youВҰ77216 all.\wj*
\v 15 \wj Everything that the fatherВҰ77221 has is mine, that's why I saidВҰ77226 he will take what is mine and explain it to you.\wj*
\s1 A brief upset coming followed by happiness
\rem /s1 Sadness and Gladness
\rem /s1 Sadness Will Be Turned to Joy
\rem /s1 Sorrow Will Turn into Joy
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj It won't be much longerВҰ77238 and you won't be able to see me any more, and then a little while after that, and you'll see me againВҰ77243.вҖқ\wj*
\rem /s1 The Disciples' Grief Will Turn to Joy
\p
\v 17 \wj This got hisВҰ77259 followers asking each other, вҖңWhat'sВҰ77262 all this about seeing him for not much longer, and then seeing him againВҰ77276 after a while? And why does he say he's goingВҰ77285 to the fatherВҰ77288?\wj*вҖқ
\v 18 SoВҰ77290 they were saying, вҖңWhat'sВҰ77292 this about вҖҳnot much longerвҖҷ? We don'tВҰ77300 know what he means.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 However \nd Yeshua\nd* knewВҰ77306 what they wanted to ask him, and so he said to them, вҖң\wj You are trying to find out from each other what I meant when I said that you won'tВҰ77334 be able to see me after a little while, and then a little while after that you'll see me againВҰ77338.\wj*
\v 20 \wj I can assure you that you'll be weepingВҰ77348 and mourning but the worldВҰ77354 will be elatedВҰ77355. You'll be upset but then yourВҰ77362 upset will turn into happiness.\wj*
\v 21 \wj A womanВҰ77367 giving birth has pains when the delivery begins, but when she hears that the baby is born, she doesn't rememberВҰ77385 those pains any more because she's so happy that herВҰ77378 childВҰ77383 was born.\wj*
\v 22 \wj SoВҰ77402 too with all of you: you'll be upset for a while butВҰ77415 then I'llВҰ77413 be with you againВҰ77411 and you'll be so happy and no one will be able to take that happiness away from you.\wj*
\p
\v 23 вҖң\wj WhenВҰ77431 that happens, you won'tВҰ77437 be askingВҰ77438 me for anythingВҰ77449. I can assure you that whatever you requestВҰ77450 from the fatherВҰ77452 in my nameВҰ77457 andВҰ77431 my authority will be given to you.\wj*
\v 24 \wj Up until now you haven't asked \+add him\+add* for anything using myВҰ77470 authority, butВҰ77474 after that time, you'll be able to make requestsВҰ77464 and they'll be answered so that yourВҰ77479 happiness will be complete.\wj*
\s1 A new era is coming very soon
\rem /s1 Victory over the World
\rem /s1 Peace for the Disciples
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj So far I'veВҰ77486 told you these things in parables, however a time is comingВҰ77489 when I'llВҰ77506 no longerВҰ77493 be speakingВҰ77496 in parables but will tell you things about the fatherВҰ77503 quite plainlyВҰ77500.\wj*
\v 26 \wj At that time you'll have myВҰ77518 authority to requestВҰ77519 from the fatherВҰ77528. I'm not sayingВҰ77522 that I'llВҰ77525 be askingВҰ77526 him on your behalf,\wj*
\v 27 \wj no, because he himselfВҰ77532 loves you all because you have lovedВҰ77541 me and have believedВҰ77543 that I was sent by \+nd GodВҰ77549\+nd*.\wj*
\v 28 \wj I was sent out by the father and I have come into the world, butВҰ77556 I'll be leavingВҰ77563 the world again and returning to the father.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 29 Yeshua's followers responded, вҖңAh, now you'reВҰ77582 speaking plainlyВҰ77581 and not using parables.
\v 30 Finally we realise that you know everything already and don'tВҰ77593 need to ask anyoneВҰ77597 else, and so we now believeВҰ77602 that you cameВҰ77607 from \nd GodВҰ77606\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 вҖң\wj So now youВҰ77613 all believeВҰ77613?\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ77608.
\v 32 вҖң\wj The time is comingВҰ77617 and is here already when you will all be scatteredВҰ77625 in various directions and will leaveВҰ77635 me by myself, butВҰ77619 I won'tВҰ77637 be aloneВҰ77639 becauseВҰ77640 the fatherВҰ77642 is \+add always\+add* with me.\wj*
\v 33 \wj I'veВҰ77648 told you theseВҰ77646 things so that you can all have peaceВҰ77653 in me. You will have troubles in this world, but be courageousВҰ77662 because I have overcomeВҰ77664 the world.\wj*вҖқ
\c 17
\s1 Yeshua prays for his current and future followers
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays for His Disciples
\rem /s1 The Prayer of Jesus
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays for Himself
\p
\v 1 After \nd Yeshua\nd* had finished speaking, he looked up to the skyВҰ77680 and saidВҰ77682, вҖң\wj Father, it's now the time for you to honour yourВҰ77688 son so that the son can honour you.\wj*
\v 2 \wj You already gaveВҰ77699 me authorityВҰ77701 over all people so that I could grant eternalВҰ77717 lifeВҰ77716 to everyoneВҰ77705 that you'veВҰ77707 givenВҰ77707 me.\wj*
\v 3 \wj And eternalВҰ77722 lifeВҰ77723 means knowing you, the only true \+nd GodВҰ77731\+nd*, andВҰ77719 knowing meвҖ”\+nd Yeshua\+nd* the \+nd messiahВҰ77738\+nd* that you sent.\wj*
\v 4 \wj I honoured you here on the earthВҰ77748 by completingВҰ77753 everything that you gaveВҰ77756 me to do.\wj*
\v 5 \wj SoВҰ77762 fatherВҰ77767, now you yourselfВҰ77769 can honourВҰ77764 me with the greatness thatВҰ77773 I had when I was together with you beforeВҰ77777 the creation of the worldВҰ77781.\wj*
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays for His Disciples
\p
\v 6 вҖң\wj I revealedВҰ77785 your power to the ones that you gave me from this worldВҰ77799. They were yours and you gave them to me, and they have obeyed your teaching.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Now they understand that everything that you gaveВҰ77823 to me came from you,\wj*
\v 8 \wj becauseВҰ77830 I passed on to them the messagesВҰ77832 that you gaveВҰ77836 to me, and they accepted them. Now they believeВҰ77853 that I cameВҰ77851 from you and that it was you who sentВҰ77858 me here.\wj*
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj I'm asking about \+em them\+em*. It's not the people of this worldВҰ77866 that I'm asking about, but about the ones that you gaveВҰ77871 me becauseВҰ77874 they belong to you.\wj*
\v 10 \wj Everything that's mine is yours, and everything that's your is mine, and I'veВҰ77892 been honoured by their actions.\wj*
\v 11 \wj I'm about to leave this world and come to you, butВҰ77898 they will stay here in it. Holy fatherВҰ77930, use yourВҰ77937 power to keepВҰ77932 protect the ones that you gaveВҰ77954 me, so that they might be united just like you and I are one.\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 17:12: \xt Psa 41:9; Yhn 13:18.\x*\wj When I was with them, I protected them with the authority that you gaveВҰ77982, and I guardedВҰ77986 them so that not one of them perishedВҰ77992, exceptВҰ77993 the one who chose destructionВҰ77998 so that it will indeed happen as the scripturesВҰ78001 foretold.\wj*
\v 13 \wj ButВҰ78008 soon I'll be comingВҰ78007 to youВҰ78006, and I'm speakingВҰ78010 theseВҰ78009 things in the worldВҰ78014 so that theyВҰ78016 will have the same happiness as me and be fulfilledВҰ78021 in their lives.\wj*
\v 14 \wj I'veВҰ78028 passed on yourВҰ78035 teaching to them, andВҰ78038 the world hatedВҰ78041 them becauseВҰ78044 theyВҰ78046 don't belong to this world, just as I don't.\wj*
\v 15 \wj I'm not askingВҰ78061 you to remove them out of this worldВҰ78067, but rather to stop evilВҰ78074 from overcoming them.\wj*
\v 16 \wj They don't belong to this world just as I don't.\wj*
\v 17 \wj Purify them with the truthвҖ”your messageВҰ78098 is that truth.\wj*
\v 18 \wj In the same way that you sent me out into this world, so I also send them out into the world.\wj*
\v 19 \wj I'm purifying myselfВҰ78129 for their sakes so that theyВҰ78133 also may be made pure by the truthВҰ78137.\wj*
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays for All Believers
\p
\v 20 вҖң\wj But it's not just on behalf of the ones right here that I'm askingВҰ78143, butВҰ78145 also for all the others who will believeВҰ78150 that I came from you when they hear the messageВҰ78154 of theseВҰ78140 ones,\wj*
\v 21 \wj so that they will all become united, just as you, fatherВҰ78164, are in me and I am in you. I ask that they will also be in us so that the worldВҰ78180 will be able to believeВҰ78181 that it was you who sentВҰ78186 me here.\wj*
\v 22 \wj And the honour that you'veВҰ78194 given me, I'veВҰ78197 passed on to them so that theyВҰ78201 can be united just as weВҰ78205 are oneвҖ”\wj*
\v 23 \wj me in them and you in me so that they can be perfectedВҰ78220 as one. Then the worldВҰ78229 will know that you sentВҰ78233 me here and that you love them \+add just\+add* like you love me.\wj*
\p
\v 24 \wj Father, I want those that you'veВҰ78246 givenВҰ78246 me to be with me whereverВҰ78251 I am so that they'll be able to see my greatnessвҖ”the greatness that you gaveВҰ78270 me becauseВҰ78272 you lovedВҰ78273 me even beforeВҰ78275 the creation of the worldВҰ78277.\wj*
\v 25 \wj Righteous fatherВҰ78278, this worldВҰ78282 didn'tВҰ78285 know you, butВҰ78293 I know you and theseВҰ78294 ones know that you sentВҰ78299 me here.\wj*
\v 26 \wj I revealed yourВҰ78305 power and authority to them and will continue to do so, so that the love that you love me with might be in them, and I too might be in them.\wj*вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 Yeshua is arrested
\rem /s1 The trial and crucifixion of Jesus
\rem /s1 The Arrest of Jesus
\rem /s1 The Betrayal and Arrest of Jesus
\rem /s1 Jesus Arrested
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
\r (Mat. 26:47-56; Mark 14:43-50; Luke 22:47-53)
\p
\v 1 After he'd said all this, \nd Yeshua\nd* and his followers wentВҰ78329 out of Yerushalem \add proper\add* and over the Kidron streamВҰ78337 towards a gardenВҰ78344 thatВҰ78346 he and his followers entered.
\v 2 And YudasВҰ78357 (the one who would hand him over) also knew the placeВҰ78363 becauseВҰ78364 \nd Yeshua\nd* andВҰ78355 hisВҰ78374 followers oftenВҰ78365 met there.
\v 3 Meanwhile YudasВҰ78378 had met with the soldiers and servants of the chiefВҰ78385 priestsВҰ78385 and the Pharisee partyВҰ78389, and they all started comingВҰ78391 into the garden with lanternsВҰ78394 and flaming torchesВҰ78396 and weaponsВҰ78398.
\v 4 \nd Yeshua\nd* who already knew what was going to happen to himВҰ78408, came forward and asked them, вҖң\wj Who are youВҰ78416 all lookingВҰ78416 forВҰ78416?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 5 And they answeredВҰ78417, вҖңYeshuaвҖ”the one from \nd NazarethВҰ78422\nd*.вҖқ
\p Yeshua responded, вҖң\wj \+em I am\+em* the one.\wj*вҖқ
\p YudasВҰ78433, the one handing him over, was standing there among them.
\v 6 ButВҰ78450 when Yeshua had saidВҰ78441 that he is the one, they backed away and fell to the groundВҰ78452.\f + \fr 18:6 \ft TD: It's not clear from the original if they fell over backwards, or if they stepped back and then fell forward (either voluntarily or involuntarily) onto their knees.\f*
\v 7 SoВҰ78462 he askedВҰ78456 them againВҰ78453, вҖң\wj Who are you all lookingВҰ78460 forВҰ78460?\wj*вҖқ
\p And they answered, вҖң\nd Yeshua\nd*вҖ”the one from \nd NazarethВҰ78467\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj I already told you all that \+em I am\+em* the one. SoВҰ78478 if it's me that you're lookingВҰ78480 forВҰ78480, let theseВҰ78482 others leave.\wj*вҖқ
\v 9 (In this way, the statement was fulfilledВҰ78485 that Yeshua had saidВҰ78489 previously: вҖҳI didn'tВҰ78495 lose any of the ones that youВҰ78492 gaveВҰ78492 me.вҖҷ)\f + \fr 18:9 \ft TD: It's not certain from the original whether v9 was part of Mark's commentary on the events or part of Yeshua's response to the arresting party.\f*
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ78526 SimonВҰ78503 PeterВҰ78505 drew the swordВҰ78507 that he was carrying andВҰ78526 swiped at the servant of the high priestВҰ78515, cutting off hisВҰ78519 rightВҰ78524 earВҰ78521. The servant's nameВҰ78528 was MalchusВҰ78534.
\v 11 \x + \xo 18:11: \xt Mat 26:39; Mrk 14:36; Luk 22:42.\x*But \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ78535 to PeterВҰ78540, вҖң\wj Put your swordВҰ78543 back in its sheathВҰ78547. I need to proceed with the plan thatВҰ78550 the fatherВҰ78555 has prepared for meвҖ”I can'tВҰ78558 just avoid the suffering.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is taken to Annas
\rem /s1 Jesus before the High Priest
\rem /s1 Jesus Taken to Annas
\rem /s1 Annas Questions Jesus
\rem /s1 Jesus before Annas
\p
\v 12 SoВҰ78562 the soldiers and their commanderВҰ78566, and the servants of the Jewish leaders arrestedВҰ78572 \nd Yeshua\nd* and tied himВҰ78577 up.
\v 13 First theyВҰ78579 took him to AnnasВҰ78583, the father-in-law of CaiaphasВҰ78589 who was the chiefВҰ78592 priestВҰ78592 that yearВҰ78594.
\v 14 \x + \xo 18:14: \xt Yhn 11:49-50.\x*(CaiaphasВҰ78599 was the one who had suggested that itВҰ78605 was better for the peopleВҰ78612 andВҰ78597 the nation if \em one\em* manВҰ78607 should dieВҰ78608 for \add all of\add* them.)
\s1 Peter denies being a Yeshua-follower
\rem /s1 Peter's First Denial
\rem /s1 Peter Denies Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:59-66; Mark 14:55-64; Luke 22:66-71)
\rem /r (Matthew 26.69,70; Mark 14.66-68; Luke 22.55-57)
\p
\v 15 Now SimonВҰ78618 PeterВҰ78619 and another apprentice were following Yeshua, and since that otherВҰ78622 apprentice was knownВҰ78630 to the chief priest, he was allowed to enterВҰ78635 following Yeshua into the courtyardВҰ78640 of the chief priest
\v 16 while Peter waited outsideВҰ78651 at the door. Then the otherВҰ78657 apprenticeВҰ78655 who was knownВҰ78661 to the chiefВҰ78665 priestВҰ78665 wentВҰ78652 back and spokeВҰ78667 to the woman at the door and broughtВҰ78673 Peter in too.
\v 17 But the servantВҰ78684 girlВҰ78684 who was watching the door challenged PeterВҰ78689, вҖңAren't you also one of the followers of that manВҰ78698?вҖқ
\p вҖңNo, I'm not,вҖқ he responded.
\p
\v 18 Meanwhile the servants and attendantsВҰ78711 had made a fireВҰ78712 and were standing around itВҰ78716 warming themselvesВҰ78718, and PeterВҰ78725 also went and stood there to warm himselfВҰ78730.
\s1 Annas tries to interrogate Yeshua
\rem /s1 The High Priest Questions Jesus
\r (Mat. 26:59-66; Mark 14:69-72; Luke 22:58-62)
\rem /r (Matthew 26.59-66; Mark 14.55-64; Luke 22.66-71)
\p
\v 19 Now the chiefВҰ78733 priestВҰ78733 interrogated \nd Yeshua\nd* about his followers andВҰ78741 about his teachingВҰ78744.
\v 20 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ78747 himВҰ78748, вҖңI'veВҰ78752 spokenВҰ78755 openly to the people. I alwaysВҰ78759 taughtВҰ78760 in the meeting halls and in the templeВҰ78767 whereВҰ78768 Jewish people meet. I didn't speak in secretВҰ78776
\v 21 so why are youВҰ78781 askingВҰ78781 \em me\em*? Ask the people who heardВҰ78786 what I told themвҖ”they're the ones who know what I saidВҰ78794.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 WhenВҰ78797 he said that, one of the attendantsВҰ78804 standing there slapped \nd Yeshua\nd* \add on the face\add* andВҰ78797 said, вҖңYou think you can answerВҰ78812 the chiefВҰ78814 priestВҰ78814 like that?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 But \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖңIf I said anything wrongВҰ78823, tell me my error. But if it was true, why are youВҰ78835 hitting me?вҖқ
\p
\v 24 SoВҰ78838 AnnasВҰ78841 sentВҰ78836 himВҰ78839 away, still tied up, to CaiaphasВҰ78844 the chiefВҰ78846 priestВҰ78846.
\s1 Peter again denies following Yeshua
\rem /s1 Peter's Second and Third Denials
\rem /s1 Peter Denies Jesus Again
\r (Mat. 26:71-75; Mark 14:69-72; Luke 22:58-62)
\p
\v 25 SimonВҰ78849 PeterВҰ78850 was still standing by the fire warmingВҰ78853 himselfВҰ78853 when he was asked, вҖңAren't you also one of hisВҰ78863 followers?вҖқ
\p ButВҰ78848 he denied it, saying, вҖңNo, I'm not.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 One of the servants of the chiefВҰ78880 priestВҰ78880 who was a relativeВҰ78881 of the man whose earВҰ78887 PeterВҰ78885 had cut off said, вҖңDidn't I see youВҰ78890 in the gardenВҰ78894 with that Yeshua?вҖқ
\p
\v 27 ButВҰ78902 PeterВҰ78901 againВҰ78897 denied it, andВҰ78902 just then a roosterВҰ78904 crowedВҰ78905.
\s1 Pilate interrogates Yeshua
\rem /s1 Jesus Before Pilate
\rem /s1 Jesus' Trial before Pilate
\rem /s1 Jesus before Pilate
\r (Mat. 26:71-75; Mark 14:69-72; Luke 22:58-62)
\rem /r (Matthew 27.1,2,11-14; Mark 15.1-5; Luke 23.1-5)
\p
\v 28 ThenВҰ78920 they led \nd Yeshua\nd* out from Caiaphas' place and towards the residence of the governor. It was now the earlyВҰ78919 hours of the morning and as Jews, they didn'tВҰ78922 enter the residence of the Roman governor so they wouldn't become defiledВҰ78929 and thus unable to eatВҰ78932 the Passover meal.
\v 29 SoВҰ78936 Governor PilateВҰ78940 cameВҰ78935 outsideВҰ78941 to them andВҰ78945 asked, вҖңWhat charge are youВҰ78950 all bringingВҰ78950 againstВҰ78951 this manВҰ78953?вҖқ
\p
\v 30 вҖңWe wouldn'tВҰ78969 have brought him to you if he hadn't committed a serious crime,вҖқ they answeredВҰ78955.
\p
\v 31 SoВҰ78976 PilateВҰ78979 said, вҖңYou just take him and judgeВҰ78989 him yourselves accordingВҰ78985 to yourВҰ78988 own laws.вҖқ
\p ButВҰ78984 the Jewish leaders respondedВҰ78975, вҖңWe don'tВҰ78998 have permissionВҰ78999 to execute anyoneВҰ79001.вҖқ
\v 32 (This happened to fulfilВҰ79009 what \nd Yeshua\nd* had said\x + \xo 18:32: \xt Yhn 3:14; 12:32.\x* about the way that he was goingВҰ79017 to die.)
\p
\v 33 So PilateВҰ79027 wentВҰ79019 back into his governor'sВҰ79024 residenceВҰ79024 and calledВҰ79029 for \nd Yeshua\nd* and asked himВҰ79034, вҖңSo you're the kingВҰ79039 of the Jews?вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj Are you sayingВҰ79053 this yourselfВҰ79049,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* asked, вҖң\wj or did othersВҰ79056 say itВҰ79058 about me?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 PilateВҰ79065 retorted, вҖңHoy! I'm not a Jew. It was your own people and the chiefВҰ79079 priestsВҰ79079 that handed you over to me. What have you done?вҖқ
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj My kingdom isn't in this world,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ79086, вҖң\wj because if it was, my supporters would have fought so that I wouldn't have been handed over to the Jewish leaders. But no, my kingdom isn't from here.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 37 вҖңSoВҰ79137 you \em are\em* a king then?вҖқ PilateВҰ79140 respondedВҰ79136.
\p вҖң\wj You're sayingВҰ79152 that I'm a king,\wj*вҖқ said \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj and indeed I was born to be a king. I came into the worldВҰ79169 so that I could testifyВҰ79171 to the truth.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 38 вҖң\add Yeah.\add* What is truthВҰ79196?вҖқ said PilateВҰ79192.
\s1 Pilate gives permission to execute an innocent man
\rem /s1 Jesus Sentenced to Death
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Sentenced to Death
\r (Mat. 27:15-31; Mark 15:6-20; Luke 23:13-25)
\p After he'd said this, Pilate wentВҰ79201 back outside to the Jews andВҰ79197 told them, вҖңI can'tВҰ79209 find anything that he's guilty of.
\v 39 But you all have a customВҰ79218 here that the governor can release one prisoner during the Passover. So would you like me to release the kingВҰ79236 of the Jews?вҖқ
\p
\v 40 ButВҰ79250 theyВҰ79239 all yelledВҰ79239 back, вҖңNo, not this one. Release Barabbas.вҖқ (Barabbas was a robberВҰ79253.)
\c 19
\rem /s1 Jesus Sentenced to Death
\rem /s1 Jesus Sentenced to be Crucified
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ79255 PilateВҰ79259 tookВҰ79256 \nd YeshuaВҰ79262\nd* andВҰ79263 had him floggedВҰ79264.
\v 2 ThenВҰ79265 the soldiersВҰ79267 twistedВҰ79268 some thornВҰ79271 branches togetherВҰ79268 into a crownВҰ79269 and put itВҰ79273 on Yeshua's headВҰ79279, and they dressed him in a \add royal\add* purpleВҰ79283 robeВҰ79282.
\v 3 They came up to him and said, вҖңGreetingsВҰ79292, you kingВҰ79294 of the Jews,вҖқ and thenВҰ79297 slapped him.
\p
\v 4 ThenВҰ79301 PilateВҰ79307 wentВҰ79302 back outsideВҰ79305 andВҰ79301 said to the Jews, вҖңLookВҰ79312 here. I'm bringingВҰ79313 him out to you so that you all can knowВҰ79318 that I didn'tВҰ79329 find him guiltyВҰ79326 of anything.вҖқ
\v 5 SoВҰ79348 they led \nd Yeshua\nd* out wearingВҰ79339 the thornyВҰ79342 crownВҰ79343 and the kingly robeВҰ79347, and Pilate said, вҖңLookВҰ79351. Here's the manВҰ79354.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 Now when the chiefВҰ79360 priestsВҰ79360 and their supporters sawВҰ79357 him, they yelledВҰ79365 out, вҖңExecute him on a stake! Execute him on a stake!вҖқ
\p вҖңWell you take him and executeВҰ79380 him on a stake,вҖқ PilateВҰ79374 answered, вҖңbecauseВҰ79382 I haven't found anything that he's guiltyВҰ79388 of.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 The Jews responded, вҖңWe have a law and he should be executed accordingВҰ79397 to that law becauseВҰ79403 he said he was the son of \nd GodВҰ79407\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 Now when PilateВҰ79415 heardВҰ79413 that, he became more afraidВҰ79421.
\v 9 SoВҰ79422 he wentВҰ79423 back inside the residenceВҰ79426 andВҰ79422 asked Yeshua, вҖңWhere do you come from?вҖқ
\p ButВҰ79422 Yeshua didn'tВҰ79441 answerВҰ79440 him.
\v 10 SoВҰ79445 PilateВҰ79448 said, вҖңWhy don'tВҰ79450 you answer me? Don't you realise that I have the authority to release you and I also have the authority to have you executedВҰ79463 on a stakeВҰ79463?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj You have no authorityВҰ79474 over me,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ79467, вҖң\wj none at all, exceptВҰ79479 what has been granted to you from aboveВҰ79485. BecauseВҰ79486 of this, the sinВҰ79494 of the person who handed me over to you is greaterВҰ79493.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 After hearing this, PilateВҰ79500 wanted to release him butВҰ79506 the Jews yelledВҰ79508 out, вҖңIf you release thatВҰ79523 man, you'reВҰ79518 no friend of Caesar. EveryoneВҰ79522 who claims to be a king is no friend of Caesar's.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 SoВҰ79533 now Pilate, havingВҰ79535 heardВҰ79535 all this, broughtВҰ79542 \nd Yeshua\nd* outsideВҰ79543 \add again\add*. Pilate satВҰ79548 down on the judge's seat at a placeВҰ79553 called The StoneВҰ79555 PavementВҰ79555 (andВҰ79547 called GabbathaВҰ79560 in Hebrew).
\v 14 It was now aboutВҰ79570 noon on the dayВҰ79564 when the Passover meal is preparedВҰ79564, andВҰ79563 Pilate said to the Jews, вҖңLookВҰ79578. Here's yourВҰ79581 kingВҰ79580.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 They yelledВҰ79585 back, вҖңTake him away. Take him away. ExecuteВҰ79590 him on a stake.вҖқ
\p PilateВҰ79595 asked them, вҖңYou want me to have yourВҰ79598 king executedВҰ79599 on a stake?вҖқ
\p вҖңWe don'tВҰ79603 have any king other than CaesarВҰ79608,вҖқ the chief priestsВҰ79602 answeredВҰ79600.
\p
\v 16 SoВҰ79621 Pilate gaveВҰ79611 them his permission and handed \nd Yeshua\nd* over to them, and they tookВҰ79619 him away to be executedВҰ79616 on a stakeВҰ79616.
\s1 Yeshua is hung on a stake
\rem /s1 The Crucifixion
\rem /s1 The Crucifixion of Jesus
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Crucified
\r (Mat. 27:32-44; Mark 15:21-32; Luke 23:26-43)
\p
\v 17 Carrying the pole\f + \fr 19:17 \ft TD: The Greek word used here is used in other places to mean a stake such as used to make a fence. It's uncertain whether or not it had a horizontal cross-piece, although the Romans did use a range of methods.\f* himselfВҰ79634, Yeshua arrived at the Place of the Skull (called GolgothaВҰ79650 in Hebrew) just out of the city
\v 18 whereВҰ79651 they secured him to a stake along with twoВҰ79658 othersВҰ79657вҖ”one stake on each side and with \nd YeshuaВҰ79666\nd* on the middleВҰ79663 one.
\v 19 PilateВҰ79672 wroteВҰ79667 out a titleВҰ79670 andВҰ79673 put itВҰ79679 on the stakeВҰ79678: \nd Yeshua\nd* from \nd NazarethВҰ79684\nd*, the kingВҰ79686 of the Jews.
\v 20 Many Jews read this titleВҰ79693 becauseВҰ79699 the placeВҰ79703 whereВҰ79708 \nd Yeshua\nd* was executedВҰ79709 was near the cityВҰ79705, and itВҰ79713 had been writtenВҰ79714 in Hebrew, LatinВҰ79717, and Greek.
\v 21 But the Jewish chiefВҰ79725 priestsВҰ79725 complained to PilateВҰ79723, вҖңDon't write вҖҳThe king of the JewsвҖҷ, but rather вҖҳThe one who \em said\em* he was king of the JewsвҖҷ.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 However PilateВҰ79745 answeredВҰ79743, вҖңWhat I've written, I've written.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 After the soldiersВҰ79751 had fastened \nd Yeshua\nd* to the stakeВҰ79754, they tookВҰ79758 his clothesВҰ79760 andВҰ79773 placed them in fourВҰ79764 piles, one for each of them. This left his robe, which had been wovenВҰ79780 from top to bottom in one piece.
\v 24 So they said to each other, вҖңRather than tearing this, let's throw a dice to see who will get it.вҖқ (This fulfilledВҰ79800 what was written in the scripturesВҰ79799\x + \xo 19:24: \xt Psa 22:18.\x* that said: they dividedВҰ79803 my garments among themselvesВҰ79808 and threwВҰ79814 a dice for my clothesВҰ79806.) So they went ahead and did that.
\p
\v 25 Meanwhile a group of women had stayed standing near \nd Yeshua\nd* on the stakeВҰ79826: his mother and his aunt, Maria the wife of ClopasВҰ79841, and Maria from MagdalaВҰ79845.
\v 26 When \nd Yeshua\nd* saw his mother and also the apprenticeВҰ79854 that he loved standing nearby, he said to her, вҖң\wj Look, he'll be yourВҰ79868 son.\wj*вҖқ
\v 27 And to the apprentice he said, вҖң\wj LookВҰ79873, she'll be yourВҰ79877 motherВҰ79876.\wj*вҖқ And that apprentice tookВҰ79884 her into his own \add home\add* from thenВҰ79878 on.
\s1 Yeshua gives up his life on the stake
\rem /s1 The Death of Jesus
\r (Mat. 27:45-56; Mark 15:33-41; Luke 23:44-49)
\p
\v 28 Having done this, \nd Yeshua\nd* knew that everything had been accomplishedВҰ79903, and (in orderВҰ79904 for the scripturesВҰ79908\x + \xo 19:28: \xt Psa 69:21; 22:15.\x* to be fulfilledВҰ79903) said, вҖң\wj I'm thirstyВҰ79910.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 29 There was a container lyingВҰ79914 thereВҰ79921 full of vinegary wine, so they placed a spongeВҰ79920 on a hyssopВҰ79926 stalkВҰ79926, soaked it in the wine, and held it up to his mouthВҰ79931.
\v 30 After \nd Yeshua\nd* had sucked some wine out, he saidВҰ79939, вҖң\wj It is finishedВҰ79940.\wj*вҖқ ThenВҰ79941 he bowedВҰ79942 his headВҰ79944 andВҰ79941 gaveВҰ79945 up his spiritВҰ79948.
\s1 Yeshua's side is pierced with a spear
\rem /s1 Jesus' Side Is Pierced
\p
\v 31 Now because it was the preparationВҰ79953 day\x + \xo 19:31: \xt Yhn 19:14.\x* for the coming Rest Day, the Jews didn'tВҰ79956 want the bodiesВҰ79962 to remainВҰ79957 on the stakesВҰ79960 after dusk (because it was even a special Rest Day.) SoВҰ79950 they askedВҰ79978 PilateВҰ79981 to command for their legs to be brokenВҰ79983 \add to hasten their deaths\add* and then they could be takenВҰ79988 down \add sooner\add*.
\v 32 SoВҰ79990 the soldiersВҰ79992 cameВҰ79989 and brokeВҰ79997 the legs of the men on each side of Yeshua,
\v 33 but when they got to him, they sawВҰ80012 that he was alreadyВҰ80015 dead so they didn'tВҰ80019 break hisВҰ80021 legs.
\v 34 Instead one of the soldiersВҰ80027 stabbed hisВҰ80029 side with a spearВҰ80028 and immediatelyВҰ80036 bloodВҰ80037 and waterВҰ80039 cameВҰ80035 out.
\v 35 The one who actually saw this happen\f + \fr 9:35 \ft Believed to be the author of this account.\f* has testifiedВҰ80043 this andВҰ80040 hisВҰ80047 account is accurate so that you \add readers\add* can also believeВҰ80062 it,
\v 36 becauseВҰ80065 theseВҰ80066 things also happened to fulfilВҰ80070 what was written in the scripturesВҰ80069,\x + \xo 19:36: \xt Exo 12:46; Num 9:12; Psa 34:20.\x* that вҖҳnone of hisВҰ80075 bones will be brokenВҰ80073,вҖҷ
\v 37 andВҰ80076 in anotherВҰ80078 place,\x + \xo 19:37: \xt Zech 12:10; Rev 1:7.\x* вҖҳthey will look at the one that they piercedВҰ80084.вҖҷ
\s1 The wrapping and laying of Yeshua's body
\rem /s1 The Burial of Jesus
\r (Mat. 27:57-61; Mark 15:42-47; Luke 23:50-56)
\p
\v 38 After all of this, Yosef from ArimatheaВҰ80095 went to Pilate. (Yosef was a follower of Yeshua, butВҰ80086 secretly becauseВҰ80102 he was afraid of what the Jewish leaders might do.) He askedВҰ80088 Pilate for permissionВҰ80114 to remove \nd Yeshua's\nd* body, and it was granted to him so they went and got his body.
\v 39 \x + \xo 19:39: \xt Yhn 3:1-2.\x*NicodemusВҰ80132 (the one who had firstВҰ80142 visited Yeshua at nightВҰ80140) also cameВҰ80129, bringingВҰ80143 around 30kg of burial spices.
\v 40 SoВҰ80155 they tookВҰ80154 \nd Yeshua's\nd* bodyВҰ80157 and wrapped itВҰ80163 around with linenВҰ80165 strips with the spicesВҰ80169 as per the Jewish burial customsВҰ80171.
\v 41 There was a garden out at the placeВҰ80181 whereВҰ80182 Yeshua had been executedВҰ80183, andВҰ80185 in the garden thereВҰ80177 was a new tombВҰ80189 thatВҰ80192 hadn't been used yet.
\v 42 SoВҰ80200 because it was the preparationВҰ80203 dayВҰ80203 and because the tombВҰ80210 was nearby, theyВҰ80212 laid his body in thereВҰ80199.
\c 20
\s1 The body is missing from the chamber
\rem /s1 The Empty Tomb
\rem /s1 The resurrection
\rem /s1 The Resurrection
\rem /s1 The Resurrection of Jesus
\r (Mat. 28:1-8; Mark 16:1-8; Luke 24:1-12)
\p
\v 1 The following Sunday, MariaВҰ80220 from MagdalaВҰ80222 went out to the tomb very earlyВҰ80224 when it was stillВҰ80226 dark, andВҰ80216 she saw that the stoneВҰ80235 had been removed from the entrance.
\v 2 SoВҰ80244 she ran quickly and went to SimonВҰ80249 PeterВҰ80250 and the otherВҰ80254 apprenticeВҰ80255 that \nd Yeshua\nd* loved, and told them, вҖңThey've taken the \nd master'sВҰ80265\nd* \add body\add* out of the tombВҰ80268 and we don'tВҰ80270 know whereВҰ80272 they've put it.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 SoВҰ80276 PeterВҰ80278 and the otherВҰ80281 apprenticeВҰ80282 wentВҰ80275 out to the tombВҰ80287.
\v 4 They were runningВҰ80289 togetherВҰ80293, butВҰ80290 the otherВҰ80297 apprenticeВҰ80298 was a bit faster than PeterВҰ80303 andВҰ80290 so he got to the tombВҰ80310 firstВҰ80306.
\v 5 Without going in, he stoopedВҰ80313 down at the entrance and looked in and saw the linenВҰ80317 strips lyingВҰ80315 thereВҰ80315.
\v 6 ButВҰ80328 PeterВҰ80329 cameВҰ80333 along behind himВҰ80331 and wentВҰ80333 straight into the tombВҰ80336 and also saw the linenВҰ80340 strips lyingВҰ80341 thereВҰ80341.
\v 7 ButВҰ80342 the piece of clothВҰ80354 thatВҰ80345 had been on the headВҰ80349 wasn't lyingВҰ80355 thereВҰ80355 with the linenВҰ80354 strips, butВҰ80356 had been folded andВҰ80342 placedВҰ80361 separatelyВҰ80357.
\v 8 SoВҰ80363 now the otherВҰ80367 apprenticeВҰ80368 who had arrived firstВҰ80371 also wentВҰ80364 inside and he sawВҰ80376 it all and believedВҰ80378 \add thatВҰ80369 Yeshua had risen\add*.
\v 9 (At that time theyВҰ80381 weren't yet aware of the scriptureВҰ80384 about himВҰ80387 coming back to life.)
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
\v 10 SoВҰ80392 theyВҰ80391 wentВҰ80391 back againВҰ80393 to their homes.
\s1 Yeshua reveals himself to Maria from Magdala
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
\r (Mat. 28:9-10; Mark 16:9-11)
\p
\v 11 But MariaВҰ80399 had stayed there outsideВҰ80408 the tomb weeping. But when she stoopedВҰ80414 down and looked into the tomb,
\v 12 she saw twoВҰ80420 messengersВҰ80421 dressed in whiteВҰ80424 sittingВҰ80425 thereвҖ”one at the headВҰ80429 end and one at the feetВҰ80434 end of the slab whereВҰ80435 \nd Yeshua'sВҰ80440\nd* bodyВҰ80438 had been lyingВҰ80436.
\v 13 They spoke to herВҰ80443, вҖңWomanВҰ80445, why are youВҰ80447 crying?вҖқ
\p вҖңBecauseВҰ80453 they've taken away myВҰ80457 \nd masterВҰ80456\nd*,вҖқ she replied, вҖңandВҰ80458 I don'tВҰ80459 know whereВҰ80461 they've put himВҰ80464.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \nd Then\nd* she turnedВҰ80468 back around and saw \nd Yeshua\nd* standing there, butВҰ80472 she didn'tВҰ80479 realise who it was.
\v 15 \nd Yeshua\nd* asked her, вҖң\wj WomanВҰ80490, why are you crying? Who are you lookingВҰ80494 forВҰ80494?\wj*вҖқ
\p Maria assumed he might be the gardenerВҰ80500, so she answered, вҖңMisterВҰ80504, if you took the body, tell me whereВҰ80515 you put it and I'llВҰ80520 get it taken away \add for you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \nd Yeshua\nd* just answered, вҖң\wj MariaВҰ80528.\wj*вҖқ
\p She spun around and said, вҖңMy teacher!вҖқ (вҖҳRabboniВҰ80535вҖҷ in Hebrew.)
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj Don't touchВҰ80546 me,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* said to her, вҖң\wj becauseВҰ80549 I haven't gone back up to the father yet, butВҰ80562 go and tell my brothersВҰ80560 that I'm going up to my father and the father of you all, and my god and the god of you all.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 18 So MariaВҰ80581 went and told the apprenticesВҰ80588, вҖңI'veВҰ80591 seenВҰ80591 the \nd masterВҰ80594\nd*,вҖқ and she told them what he'd saidВҰ80598.
\s1 Yeshua appears to his followers
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to the Disciples
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to His Disciples
\r (Mat. 28:16-20; Mark 16:14-18; Luke 24:36-49)
\p
\v 19 On Sunday eveningВҰ80604 \nd Yeshua's\nd* apprenticesВҰ80620 had met together and had the doorsВҰ80615 locked becauseВҰ80622 they were afraid of the Jewish leaders, butВҰ80613 Yeshua arrived and stoodВҰ80631 in the middle of the room and said, вҖң\wj PeaceВҰ80638 to youВҰ80639 all.\wj*вҖқ
\v 20 ThenВҰ80640 he showedВҰ80644 them his handsВҰ80648 and his side and they were so happy now that they had seenВҰ80659 the \nd masterВҰ80661\nd*.
\v 21 \nd Yeshua\nd* continuedВҰ80662, вҖң\wj PeaceВҰ80669 to you all. Now I'm sendingВҰ80677 you all out just like the fatherВҰ80675 sentВҰ80672 me out.\wj*вҖқ
\v 22 ThenВҰ80681 he breathedВҰ80684 on them andВҰ80681 saidВҰ80683, вҖң\wj ReceiveВҰ80689 the holy \+nd spiritВҰ80690\+nd*.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 20:23: \xt Mat 16:19; 18:18.\x*\wj If you forgiveВҰ80696 anyone's sinsВҰ80698, then they'll be forgivenВҰ80699 but if you withhold forgiveness, then it will be withheld.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Thomas sees the evidence for himself
\rem /s1 Jesus and Thomas
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Thomas
\p
\v 24 But ThomasВҰ80712, one of the twelveВҰ80717 (nicknamed вҖҳTwinвҖҷ), wasn't with them when \nd Yeshua\nd* had come
\v 25 so the otherВҰ80734 apprenticesВҰ80735 told him, вҖңWe have seenВҰ80737 the \nd masterВҰ80739\nd*.вҖқ
\p ButВҰ80771 he replied, вҖңI won'tВҰ80745 believeВҰ80800 that unless I seeВҰ80746 the mark of the nails in his handsВҰ80752 and I can put my fingerВҰ80775 into the marks and can put my handВҰ80792 into \add the gash on\add* his side.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 Eight daysВҰ80803 later, \nd Yeshua's\nd* apprenticesВҰ80809 were againВҰ80805 together insideВҰ80807, andВҰ80801 \add this timeВҰ80803\add* ThomasВҰ80813 was with them.
\v 27 Yeshua came and stood in the middle of the room even though the doors were shut, and said, вҖң\wj Peace to you all.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 28 Thomas spoke up, вҖңMyВҰ80884 \nd masterВҰ80883\nd* and myВҰ80884 \nd godВҰ80887\nd*!вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖң\wj So you believe now because you'veВҰ80896 seen me,\wj*вҖқ said \nd Yeshua\nd*. вҖң\wj The ones who haven't seen me, butВҰ80907 who believe anyway, will \+add certainly\+add* be rewarded.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Why this document was written
\rem /s1 The Purpose of This Book
\rem /s1 Purpose of the Book
\p
\v 30 \nd YeshuaВҰ80918\nd* went on to do many otherВҰ80913 miracles in front of hisВҰ80922 apprenticesВҰ80921 whichВҰ80923 aren'tВҰ80924 recorded in this account.
\v 31 ButВҰ80951 what has been writtenВҰ80934 here has been recorded so that you might all believe that \nd Yeshua\nd* is the \nd messiahВҰ80944\nd*, God's son, and then by believing, so that you might have \add true\add* lifeВҰ80954 through hisВҰ80961 power.
\c 21
\s1 The miracle of the net full of fish
\rem /s1 Jesus Appears to Seven Disciples
\rem /s1 Jesus and the Miraculous Catch of Fish
\p
\v 1 AfterВҰ80962 all this, \nd Yeshua\nd* revealed himself againВҰ80968 to his apprenticesВҰ80973 at Lake Galilee. It happened like this:
\v 2 Simon PeterВҰ80986, ThomasВҰ80988 nicknamed вҖҳTwinвҖҷ, \nd NathanaelВҰ80993\nd* from CanaВҰ80998 in GalileeВҰ81000, the sonsВҰ81002 of ZebedeeВҰ81006, and twoВҰ81015 otherВҰ81009 apprenticesВҰ81012 had gathered togetherВҰ80984
\v 3 \x + \xo 21:3: \xt Luk 5:5.\x*when Simon PeterВҰ81020 said that he was goingВҰ81021 fishingВҰ81022 and the others said that they'd join him.
\p So they wentВҰ81031 off and got in the boatВҰ81038, butВҰ81033 they didn't catch anything that nightВҰ81044.
\p
\v 4 \nd When\nd* the dawn was approaching, \nd Yeshua\nd* was standing there on the shoreВҰ81061, butВҰ81051 they didn'tВҰ81062 know that itВҰ81070 was him.
\v 5 He called out, вҖң\wj Hey, young fellas. Don't youВҰ81082 have any fishВҰ81081?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңNone.вҖқ they answeredВҰ81083.
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 21:6: \xt Luk 5:6.\x*ThenВҰ81087 he said, вҖң\wj Throw the net out over the rightВҰ81094 side of the boatВҰ81097 and you'll find some.\wj*вҖқ SoВҰ81087 they did it and they caught so many fish that the net was too heavy to pull back in.
\p
\v 7 Now the apprenticeВҰ81149 that \nd Yeshua\nd* loved said to Peter, вҖңIt's the master!вҖқ When SimonВҰ81161 Peter heardВҰ81164 that, he put on his robe (becauseВҰ81173 he didn't have it on), and jumped overboard into the lakeВҰ81181.
\v 8 The otherВҰ81184 apprenticesВҰ81185 followed in the littleВҰ81188 boatВҰ81188 draggingВҰ81203 the netВҰ81205 behind them becauseВҰ81192 theyВҰ81193 were only aboutВҰ81199 100m out from the shore.
\v 9 When they went up the beach, they saw some breadВҰ81222 there and a charcoalВҰ81216 fireВҰ81216 with fishВҰ81219 cooking on itВҰ81220
\v 10 and \nd YeshuaВҰ81226\nd* told them, вҖң\wj BringВҰ81227 some of the fishВҰ81231 thatВҰ81232 youВҰ81233 just caughtВҰ81233.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 11 SoВҰ81237 SimonВҰ81238 PeterВҰ81239 went and draggedВҰ81241 the net up onto the beach. Amazingly it hadn't torn even though it contained 153 largeВҰ81254 fish.
\v 12 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* said, вҖң\wj Now, come and have breakfastВҰ81270.\wj*вҖқ But none of the apprenticesВҰ81276 dared to ask who he was, because they figured it must be the \nd masterВҰ81285\nd*.
\v 13 \nd Yeshua\nd* brought the breadВҰ81294 to them and shared it around, and then likewiseВҰ81303 for the fishВҰ81302.
\p
\v 14 This was now the thirdВҰ81307 timeВҰ81307 that \nd Yeshua\nd* had appeared to his apprenticesВҰ81312 since he'd come back to life.
\s1 Yeshua questions Peter
\rem /s1 Jesus Challenges Peter
\rem /s1 Jesus and Peter
\rem /s1 Jesus Reinstates Peter
\p
\v 15 While they were eating, Yeshua asked Simon PeterВҰ81325, вҖң\wj Simon, son of Yohan, do you love me more than theseВҰ81335?\wj*вҖқ
\p Peter answered, вҖңYes, \nd masterВҰ81339\nd*, you know that I love you.вҖқ
\p Yeshua responded, вҖң\wj Feed myВҰ81353 lambsВҰ81352.\wj*вҖқ
\v 16 Then he asked againВҰ81357, вҖң\wj SimonВҰ81363, son of Yohan, do you love me?\wj*вҖқ
\p Peter replied, вҖңYes, \nd masterВҰ81371\nd*, you know that I love you.вҖқ
\p Yeshua responded, вҖң\wj Shepherd myВҰ81384 sheepВҰ81382.\wj*вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ81407 he asked a third time, вҖң\wj SimonВҰ81389, son of Yohan, do you love me?\wj*вҖқ
\p PeterВҰ81398 was now upset that he'd been asked a third time if he loved him, andВҰ81407 he answered, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ81411\nd*, you know everything.вҖқ
\p вҖң\wj Feed myВҰ81430 sheep,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ81400.
\v 18 вҖң\wj I can assure you that while you are youngВҰ81438, you dress yourselfВҰ81440 and go wherever you want to go, butВҰ81441 as you age, you'll be stretchingВҰ81448 out yourВҰ81453 handsВҰ81451 and others will dress you and will take you where you don'tВҰ81473 want to go.\wj*вҖқ
\v 19 WhenВҰ81477 he said this, Yeshua was indicating how Peter would die honouring \nd GodВҰ81485\nd*, andВҰ81477 he told Peter, вҖң\wj Keep followingВҰ81491 me.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Jesus and the Beloved Disciple
\rem /s1 Jesus and the Other Disciple
\p
\v 20 \x + \xo 21:20: \xt Yhn 13:25.\x*When PeterВҰ81496 turnedВҰ81493 around he saw that the apprenticeВҰ81499 that Yeshua loved was followingВҰ81504 themвҖ”the one who'd leaned on \nd Yeshua's\nd* chestВҰ81513 during the supperВҰ81510 and asked who the one was who would turn Yeshua over.
\v 21 Noticing him, PeterВҰ81532 asked \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ81538\nd*, what aboutВҰ81541 that one?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 But \nd Yeshua\nd* replied, вҖң\wj If I want him to stay alive untilВҰ81551 I come back, what business would itВҰ81553 be of yours? You just stay followingВҰ81559 me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 23 As a result of that, a rumour wentВҰ81561 around the others that that one wouldn't die, but \nd Yeshua\nd* never said that. (He only said, вҖң\wj If I want him to stay alive untilВҰ81596 I come back, what business would it be of yours?\wj*вҖқ)
\s1 Statement of fact
\rem /s1 Conclusion
\p
\v 24 This author is the apprenticeВҰ81604 thatВҰ81605 testifiesВҰ81607 about these thingsвҖ”the one who wroteВҰ81613 this down and whose account is true.
\rem /s1 Conclusion
\v 25 (There were also many otherВҰ81628 things that \nd Yeshua\nd* did, whichВҰ81636 if they were all written down thenВҰ81626 even the worldВҰ81645 itselfВҰ81642 wouldn't have roomВҰ81646 for all the books that would need to be written.)
